Commentary: A gentle outswinger from Anderson. On a length and outside off, it's an easy leave for Shubman Gill.
Anderson gets closer to the off stump line, on a fuller length and shaping away, Gill covers his stumps and allows it through.
This one holds its line as it wobbles through to Billings. In the channel outside off, Gill leaves again. Sam struggles a bit as he attempts to collect.
Anderson bowls an inswinger on this occasion, around off and shaping in, Shubman Gill stands still inside the crease and makes another leave.
Angles it in, on a length and around middle and leg, Shubman Gill tries to work it on the leg side but misses. He is hit high on the front leg. A stifled appeal for an lbw dies down quickly.

FOUR! Shubman Gill opens his account with a boundary. Anderson delivers it full and around middle, nipping in off the seam, Gill leans across a bit and clips it through wide mid on for a boundary. Great timing.
Broad starts with a good-length delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone. It's called a no ball for overstepping.
A touch short and outside off, shaping in a shade, Pujara shoulders arms.
A gentle inswinger from Broad, around off, Pujara withdraws his bat late.
Makes the batter play this time. Around off, on a length, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it safely from the crease.
Hurls across a length ball outside off, Pujara covers his stumps and shoulders arms again.
This one goes on straight after landing on a length outside off, Pujara takes his front leg forward to cover the line and then allows it through to the keeper.
A bit too full this time, around middle, Pujara flicks it across the line but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Delivers it on a good length, outside off and shaping away, Shubman Gill has an easy leave to make. England have not made the batters play enough balls so far.
Jimmy goes full this time, around off and angling in, Shubman Gill gets forward and helps it to mid-wicket.

A soft outside edge but it falls just shy of Bairstow at third slip. Anderson lands it on a length and just outside off, moving in a bit, Gill hangs his bat out in defense and it goes off the outside half to the slip cordon.
Beauty to beat the bat! Fuller and close to off, Shubman Gill tries to play the angle but it nips away late to beat the outside edge. Superb by Jimmy!
Sliding down the leg side, Gill fails to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg. Sam Billings gives the chase and the batters collect two leg byes.
Some extra zip on this outswinger outside off, Shubman Gill offers no shot.
Broad serves it a touch short and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara covers the line and defends it down solidly.
This one is on a length but outside off, Pujara presses his front foot forward and shoulders arms. Good carry to the keeper this time.
FOUR! Lovely from Pujara! Fuller in length and around off, Cheteshwar Pujara strides forward with a straight bat and caresses it past the diving bowler for a boundary at long off.

Was the shot offered? Drifting down the leg side, Pujara tries to flick but it seems that he withdraws his bat at the last moment. The ball takes his pads and runs down to fine leg. They take two. Umpire Aleem Dar consults his partner on whether Cheteshwar Pujara was offering any shot and then signals leg byes. Broad is not impressed.
Edgy! Fuller and outside off, Pujara pushes at it as he gets forward and it goes off the outside edge. Doesn't carry to the slip cordon.
In the zone outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Fuller in length and around off, Shubman Gill doesn't go hard at it and just creams his drive through mid off for a boundary.
On a good length outside off, Shubman Gill makes a safe leave.
Angles in a length ball on off, Shubman Gill defends it near his front pad. There is a leg slip in place.
Fuller and on off, shaping in, Gill covers the movement and defends it with soft hands towards short mid-wicket.
Anderson goes wide of the crease and serves a length ball on off, Gill taps it down towards point and calls his partner across for a quick run.
That's a good one from Anderson! This one is bowled with a wobble seam, around off on a length, Cheteshwar Pujara stays back to push at it but gets beaten.
FOUR! Fine shot from a wonderful batter. Broad serves it short and on middle, Shubman Gill gets on top of the bounce and pulls it superbly in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Streaky! Some away movement there off the seam. Around off, Gill is squared up as he tries to defend. It hits him on the pads and deflects to the off side.

FOUR! Quietly played from the back foot. On a length and around off, Shubman Gill sticks back and offers an angled bat at it. It takes a good part of his bat and scoots past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Angles in a length ball around off, it's defended on the off side.
Uses the angle of the delivery and plays a length ball down to mid-wicket.

Inswinger from Broad. It lands on a length and outside off, curling back in a bit, Gill takes a big stride forward to cover the line and allows it through. A good start from the Indian openers so far.
Fuller and on middle, moving in, Pujara flicks it off the inner half to mid-wicket and picks up a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SECOND SLIP! A needless poke from Gill and he pays the price. Anderson hurls a length ball in the corridor of uncertainty, at 129 kph, Gill hangs on the back foot, could have left it alone but decides to feel for it inside the line. It takes a thick outside edge of his bat and flies into the hands of Zak Crawley. England's slip catching has improved a lot as was evident during the New Zealand series. Early success for the hosts.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b James Anderson

Commentary: Huge shout for an lbw! The finger stays down. Anderson dishes out an inswinger to greet the new batter. It lands around off and nips back in as Vihari fails to work it around. He is rapped on the pads but it perhaps is too high.
Inside edge saves Vihari there. Another delivery, on a length around off and shaping in, Vihari tries to defend but it takes the inside edge and strikes him on the front pad.
Fine shot! Fuller and around off, Hanuma Vihari leans forward and drives it in front of square on the off side. Collects a couple of runs.
Beaten! Excellent line from Anderson. Lands it on a length and close to off, Vihari pokes inside the line but it nips away a bit to beat the bat. End of a superb over!
Broad arrows in a full ball, around off, Cheteshwar Pujara brings his bat in front of the front pad as he blocks it out.
On a length and in the channel outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot.
Angles in a length ball around off, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it gently towards cover-point. It's in the gap and they take a single.
Jaffa! Broad serves it on a length around off and gets it to shape away with extra bounce, Hanuma Vihari has a tentative poke at it and misses.
A touch short in length and outside off, Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms.
Beaten all ends up! A cracking delivery to end the over. It's on a length and approaching the off stump, Vihari tries to defend the line but it moves away late to beat the outside edge. Top over!
Back of a length, around off, Pujaran goes on his toes, jumps a bit and hits it square of the wicket on the off side. He collects a single.
This one is on a driving length outside off, going straight on after landing, Vihari gets forward and then makes a leave.
Anderson keeps probing on and around off. Full in length and shaping away, Vihari guards his stumps and shoulders arms.
Anderson pulls his length back a bit and delivers it outside off, Hanuma Vihari shows no interest in playing at it.
Pitches it up and outside off, inviting the drive, Hanuma Vihari is content in leaving these deliveries at the moment.
Fuller and just outside off, skidding off the surface, Vihari again covers his stumps and makes a leave.
In the zone outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara gets on the front foot and then carefully leaves it alone.
Fuller and just outside off, Pujara pushes it with soft hands to covers.
On a good length and around off, this time Cheteshwar Pujara goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and just outside off, it's a good brave leave from Pujara. That wasn't too far away from the off pole.
Too full on this occasion, outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara is not going to chase it.
On a length and in the zone outside off, shaping away to leave the batter further, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Right on the money to begin with! Length and on middle, gets it to straighten just a touch. Vihari pushes it to mid on.
Nicely played! This looks like an easy-paced track! Shorter and on off, Vihari gets onto the back foot and has enough time to push it through covers for two.
Yet another one which is a little too short, angled into the pads. Hanuma Vihari looks to flick but misses, it goes off the pads towards square leg for one. Leg bye.
Well fielded! Fuller and on middle, Pujara works it towards square leg. The fielder dives to his right and saves at least two.

That is a beauty! Unplayable! Can't do a lot with that. Gets his line and length right this time does Potts. Length and on off, also gets it to straighten. Pujara is beaten as he tries to defend. Pujara does nothing wrong there but the movement almost gets him.
A good leave to end! Outside off, Pujara puts in a long stride forward and shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, this one comes back in. Vihari looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to square leg.

Direct hit and Pujara was gone! Not sure if it was a late call or Pujara was ball-watching. Sam Billings too was a touch slow in getting to the stumps. On middle, this is pushed to mid on. Vihari calls for it. Pujara takes off late. Anderson picks the ball up and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Pujara had to get the dive in but don't think that would have saved him. Had Billings collected it and whipped the bails off, it would have been a wicket for England.
Angled into middle, Pujara works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Solid! On middle, Vihari gets right behind the line and defends. Vihari was shaky at the start but looks solid now.
Yet another good leave! Length and outside off, Vihari leaves it alone. Left on length.
Really good from Broad! Got the last one to come back in and this one to shape away. The line is well outside off though. Vihari plays inside the line and lets it go to the keeper.
Another one not played at as it is bowled outside off. Quite a few harmless deliveries from the England bowlers so far.
Hit and run! Quite an easy single in the end! On middle, this is clipped to the right of mid on for a single.
On middle, good length. Vihari covers the line and keeps it out.
Another leg bye! Angled into the pads, Vihari looks to flick it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side and a run is taken.
Close! Goes full and angled into the pads. Pujara looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A harmless nut to end! Outside off, left alone.
Well adjusted! Length and around off, this lands and comes back in. Vihari takes his front pad out of the way and works it towards square leg for one.
Angled into middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Not a lot of carry again! Outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one. Sam Billings collects it near his boot.
FOUR! Put away and Pujara moves into double figures. A rare bad ball and Pujara does not let it go. Short and wide outside off, this is slapped through covers for a boundary.

EDGED AND TAKEN! PUJARA REVIEWS! NOT OUT! NOTHING ON ULTRA EDGE! It is also going over the stumps when checked for an LBW. A successful review by Pujara and a good one. Not sure why he hesitated for a second before taking the review. Coming to the delivery - This is on a length and around off, it jags back in a long way. There is a sound as it passes the inside half of the bat. Sam Billings takes it and appeals. The finger is raised. Pujara thinks for a second and reviews and in the end, he survives to fight another day.
5 from the over then! On off, Pujara taps it down from the back foot to point.

Half an appeal but that is off the thigh pad! Length and on off, this one comes back in too. Hanuma Vihari looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad. The ball loops up to Sam Billings.
Good zip off the surface there! Length and outside off, good carry to the keeper as Vihari leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Another one on a good length, defended.
Shot! Straight to the fielder though! On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
A little too wide outside off, left alone.
On a length and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Slightly short and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on off, Cheteshwar Pujara again blocks it away towards the off side.
James Anderson bowls it on off again, and Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the fielder at slips.
James Anderson serves it on a good length, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it towards the fielder at gully by going on his toes.
Slightly shorter on off and nips back in, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone. That was a tight leave.
This one lands outside off, Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms at it.
Matthew Potts bowls it just outside off, Hanuma Vihari lets it through and towards the keeper.
Shorter in length and outside off again, Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone. It's called a no ball for overstepping.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Hanuma Vihari blocks it towards the off side.
This is just outside off, Hanuma Vihari is forward in defense but is beaten by the extra nip behind this delivery.
Matthew Potts bowls it on middle, Hanuma Vihari flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.

EDGED BUT PUT DOWN! Matthew Potts delivers it on a length and close to off, holding its line, Hanuma Vihari tries to defend but it takes a thick outside edge and flies to the right of second slip. Zak Crawley reacts and tries to grab it with one hand but it pops out. Zak attempts to use his left hand to take it under control but only ends up pushing the ball away from his palm. Hanuma Vihari gets a lucky escape.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Vihari tries to play it on the leg side but it hits him on his body.
Full and on off, Vihari blocks it to to the off side.
Good leave! Anderson bowls it on a length outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.

Great from Anderson. This one lands on a length and nips into the right-hander, Vihari uncomfortably pushes it towards square leg for a single. The throw comes to the striker's end but it hits Pujara instead.
On a length and on off, Pujara punches it off his back foot to covers.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Bounce, movement, there was everything on that delivery! Beauty! Can't do a lot with that. Pujara who looked solid so far has to walk back courtesy of a special ball. This is on a length around off, it lands and moves away and also there is extra bounce. Pujara looks to defend it with soft hands. He tries to control the bounce but it goes off the shoulder of his blade to Crawley at second slip. He makes no mistake this time. India are in a spot of bother now. Out comes their saviour on many occasions, Virat Kohli, as he is the new man in.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b James Anderson

Commentary: Goes outside off, shaping away, Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
This one is just outside off and on a length, Hanuma Vihari leaves it again towards the keeper.
Goes wide outside off, shaping away, Hanuma Vihari leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Bowls it on off this time, Hanuma Vihari guides it towards the fielder at mid on.

FOUR! Fuller and down the leg side, Hanuma Vihari flicks it towards fine leg and the ball races away. Jack Leach makes a sliding stop near the fence but the umpires want to get it checked upstairs. The replays find that Leach was in contact with the ball and the boundary line at the same time.
Fuller one and on middle, Hanuma Vihari flicks it towards square leg for a brace.
Goes outside off and on a length, Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
This one lands outside off and nips in sharply, Virat Kohli shoulder arms at it. That was a tight leave.
Bowls it outside off again, Virat Kohli lets it through and towards the keeper.
Goes outside off again, Virat Kohli lets it go.
Touch fuller and on off, this is defended towards the fielder at mid off.
Goes outside off again, Virat Kohli eases it towards short cover and takes a quick single.
Good-Length delivery on the middle, sharply nips in off the surface. Virat Kohli tries to play at it but gets hit high on his body.

FOUR! Nearly drags in on! Potts has his hands up, first in hope and then in disappointment. He serves it on a length and close to off, Virat Kohli stays back to push at it but gets an inside edge. It beats the stumps and races away to fine leg for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Virat Kohli shoulders arms.
Delivers it on a good length, just outside off and getting it to move away, Kohli makes another leave.
This one is angled into the batter, from around off, Virat Kohli stays on the back foot and works it towards mid-wicket.
Another delivery in the zone outside off, Virat is not going to chase those.
Anderson lands it on a fuller length, around off, Vihari is on the front foot as he defends.
Back of a length, around off, Hanuma Vihari goes on his toes and plays it down towards point for a run.
Inward movement there, from around off and on a length. Virat gently defends it from the back foot, towards cover-point and takes a quick run.
Sharp on this occasion. Some extra zip as it lands on a length around off and goes away a bit. Hanuma Vihari keeps his bat close to his body as he lets it go.
James Anderson is mixing his variations smartly. An inswinger this time, from a length around off and beating Vihari in his defense. He gets hit high on his pads.
Fraction short in length and outside off, Hanuma Vihari goes on the back foot and steers it through backward point. Jonny Bairstow chases it down from third slip and they get three runs.
Edgy this time! Back of a length, around off, Vihari stays back to work it on the leg side but gets an outside edge. It races through the gap between slips and gully for a couple of runs.

OUT! PLUMB IN FRONT! Matthew Potts has this habit of producing wicket-taking deliveries and he has done it again. He is absolutely delighted and the crowd is also making a lot of noise. Hanuma Vihari has a shocked look on his face as he walks up to his partner but then returns without taking the DRS. He was a dead duck, to be honest. Great delivery, landing on a full length outside off and jagging back in sharply off the pitch at 127 kph. Hanuma Vihari is caught inside the crease as his attempt to flick flops. He is pinged on the pads, the appeal is made and the finger goes up. India are in a spot of bother.
Howout: lbw b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Serves it on a length, around off, Rishabh Pant pushes it defensively to covers and looks keen to pick up a run. Virat Kohli sends him back.
Streaky! Potts again lands it on a length and around off, angling away, Rishabh Pant tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller this time and around leg, Pant flicks it through square leg and gets off the mark with a single.
FOUR! In control this time. Back of a length and around middle, it's angling down too, Virat Kohli uses his wrists and nudges it down to fine leg for a boundary.

Pant will play his way! A premeditated charge from him. The delivery is on a length and around middle and off, Pant brings his bat down after walking down the track. It takes the inner edge and goes past the stumps. They cross for a run.
On a good length and outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
Fuller and close to off, Kohli defends it back towards the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Kohli punches it in front of square on the off side and picks up a single.
Beats the bat! Anderson dishes out an outswinger, around off and nipping away, Rishabh Pant tries to defend but misses.
Around leg, some extra bounce from a good length, Rishabh Pant tries to defend but misses. It goes off his thigh pad to the off side.
Serves it on a good length, around off, Kohli defends it from the back foot to the off side.

OUT! KOHLI DRAGS IT ON! A body blow to India. Matthew Potts is over the moon with his celebration. That's a massive wicket for England. Kohli departs cheaply and it's a big heartbreak for his fans also, who continue to wait for his next century. Coming to the delivery, it's on a good length and outside off, at 131 kph and Potts gets it to shape in a little. Virat Kohli strides forward to cover the stumps and then decides to leave it. He though is late in withdrawing his bat and it takes a thick inside edge before rattling the stumps behind. England are roaring in this Test match!
Howout: b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Fuller in length and around off, Shreyas Iyer pushes it defensively past the bowler and it rolls away through mid off. They take two runs.
FOUR! Width there outside off, and Shreyas Iyer cashes in. He strokes it delightfully behind square on the off side and picks up a boundary.
Around off, on a length, Shreyas defends it from the crease, off the inside half of his blade.

FOUR! This is how he bats, if it's there to be hit, he will go for it. Fuller in length and outside off, Shreyas Iyer throws his bat at it and slices it over backward point for a boundary. 10 from the over, and a wicket as well.
Bowls it on leg, Rishabh Pant flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Goes down the leg side again and on a length, Rishabh Pant looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the vacant leg gully region. They take a single.
This one lands on a length and on middle, Shreyas Iyer eases it back towards the bowler.
Shorter one on leg, Shreyas Iyer was not expecting that but does well and leaves it in the end, although unconvincingly.
On a length and on middle, Shreyas Iyer flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Rishabh Pant goes on the back foot and dabs it down to cover-point for a run.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Rishabh Pant looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge and the ball hits his pads and rolls back towards the bowler.
Goes on off again, this is blocked out solidly.
This one lands on a length and on middle, Rishabh Pant eases it towards the fielder at mid on.
Touch fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant drives it towards long off. Ben Stokes has a long chase to do and he just stops the ball before the fence. Three runs are taken.
Fuller one on middle, Shreyas Iyer eases it towards the mid on fielder.

FOUR! Lovely shot! This is what we will get with two batters known for their attacking approach. Fuller in length and outside off, Shreyas is not going to dab it around, he strides forward and thumps it through covers for a boundary.
Bowls it outside off, Rishabh Pant leaves it alone.
FOUR! This is outrageous, showing no respect to the bowler. It's on a length and outside off, Rishabh Pant runs down the track and smacks it down to long off for a boundary.
On a length and around leg, Rishabh Pant flicks it towards square leg for one.
Shorter one on off, Shreyas Iyer leaves it through and towards the keeper.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a stunning one-handed catch by Billings to get rid of Iyer who had a bright start but didn't last for long. His struggle against the short ball continues. We saw that in the white-ball format earlier this year and he falls to one now. A rib-tickler, Shreyas Iyer awkwardly looks to fend it away. It goes off the gloves and Sam Billings dives across to his left to pouch it. This partnership started off in a really good manner but has been cut short by a stunning catch. India are in real trouble now.
Howout: c Sam Billings b James Anderson

Commentary: Goes fuller and on off, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it towards the fielder at covers.
Tossed-up delivery on off, Rishabh Pant hits it towards wide mid off. A misfield by the skipper and he chases it back. A couple of runs are taken. 100 up!
Fuller and on leg, Rishabh Pant defends it towards the leg side.
Flighted up of middle, Rishabh Pant flicks it towards past short leg for a run.
Tossed-up delivery with some turn, Ravindra Jadeja defends it back towards Jack Leach.
Fuller one again with some turn, Ravindra Jadeja looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Goes fuller and on off, Ravindra Jadeja uses his feet and lofts it over mid on for a boundary. This was a perfectly timed shot from Ravindra Jadeja.
On a length and on middle, Rishabh Pant defends it solidly.

On a length and on middle, Rishabh Pant looks to flick it but gets a slight edge of his bat and it rolls towards square leg. Pant shows interest in a run but is sent back as the fielder misses his shy at the striker's end.
Slightly shorter one, Rishabh Pant looks to play at it but gets an inside edge and rolls towards fine leg. They take a single.
Bowls it on a length and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his thigh and rolls back towards the bowler.
Wayward bouncer outside off, Ravindra Jadeja leaves it alone.
Fuller one on leg, Ravindra Jadeja flicks it towards the leg side for one.
Anderson starts with a gentle inswinger, on a length and on middle, nips back in. Jadeja tries to defend but gets hit on his body.
Full and on middle, Jadeja blocks it straight back to the bowler.
Bowls it on a length and around leg, Jadeja pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
Easy leave for Jadeja. Anderson bowls on a length and on the leg side. Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
This lands on a good length on off, shaping away, Jadeja offers no shot.
Another one on off, but this one is shaping in a bit, Jadeja decides to leave it.
Good-length delivery, angling in, Pant defends it solidly.
Goes a bit full around off, Pant leans forward and pushes it to short covers. They get across for a quick single.
Broad loses his line this time. Goes full and outside the leg stump. It was an easy leave for Jadeja.
Full and on off, Jadeja tries to block it but gets an outside edge. It does not carry to the second slip fielder. Lucky escape for him.

NOT OUT! The ball did touch the ground! Jadeja survives. Broad is not happy about it but it is the right decision. That is a beauty of a delivery though. Trademark Broad. From around the wicket, angles it into the batter. The ball lands on off and then moves away. It takes the outside edge as Jadeja tries to defend. It goes between the keeper and first slip. Billings dives but it is out of his reach. Root does well to keep his eyes on the ball and takes it inches above the surface. He then dives to his right to control the ball. They appeal but Root is unsure. Umpire Aleem Dar takes it upstairs with the soft signal being NOT OUT! Broad is not happy but the replays show that Root did not get his fingers underneath completely.
Broad goes full and outside off, Jadeja crunches it towards short covers. There is a bit of a misfield by Stokes and the batter gets a single.
A bit short around middle and leg, Jadeja flicks it straight to square leg.
Bowls it on a length on off, this one holds its line. Jadeja lifts his bat and lets it go.
This lands full and outside off, Jadeja tries to drive at it but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards the square leg fielder.

Anderson bowls this one on leg, angling it in. Jadeja tries to play at it but gets hit on his pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Ben Stokes doesn't get convinced by anyone for the DRS. The replays later show that it had pitched outside leg.
Goes full and outside off, Jadeja pushes it towards covers for a single.
Great bowling again. This one lands on middle and nips back in sharply, Pant is caught in his crease and gets hit on his body.
FOUR! Lovely Shot. Broad bowls it full, angling in. Jadeja leans forward and helps it past mid on for a boundary. Great timing.
Full again and on the middle, Jadeja flicks it but could not find the gap.
Broad leaking runs. This one lands full around middle and leg, Jadeja flicks it between the mid-wicket and mid on fielders. They get three runs.
On a length and on middle and off, Pant blocks it to the off side.
Bowls it full and outside off, Pant tries to guide it but gets an outside edge and the ball goes to gully.
FOUR! Another great shot from Pant. Broad goes full again outside off, Pant drives it through extra cover for a boundary. 11 runs from that over.

FOUR! The pitch seems to have eased out a bit and Anderson is not getting to move around a lot. Fuller and around middle, Ravindra Jadeja shows the full face of the bat and forces it past mid on for a boundary.
Fuller again, this time around leg, Jadeja clips it down to fine leg for a run.
This is some excellent batting from the pair. Fullish and around middle, Rishabh Pant flicks it through mid-wicket and the fielder gives the chase. He pulls it back near the fence and saves one run.
On a length and around leg, Jadeja taps it down off the pads to square leg and steals a single.
Anderson goes very full and around leg, Pant drives it down but finds mid on this time.
Fuller and around middle, Pant defends it watchfully to end the over. This probably will be the last over of this spell for Jimmy.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Jadeja covers his stumps and allows it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Another glorious drive from Jadeja. Too full from Broad, around off, Ravindra Jadeja leans forward and strokes it past mid off for a boundary.
Gets beaten on this occasion. Seems that's the plan. Broad dishes out another full ball, outside off, luring the batter, Jadeja attempts to drive but misses.
Serves it on a good length, just outside off and angling in a bit, Jadeja leaves.
Broad bowls it full and wide outside off, shaping away late, Ravindra Jadeja decides not to chase it.
Puts it on a length and outside off, shaping away a hint, Ravindra Jadeja again offers no shot.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter this time, around off and a bit short, Pant defends it safely.
FOUR! Here comes Pant down the track and here it goes to the fence. A flighted ball, full and outside off, Pant skips down the track and hammers it to the long off fence.

FOUR! Mind games going on at the moment and Pant is winning it. The last shot prompted the bowler to go short, it's around off, Rishabh Pant anticipates it and pulls it from the back foot through backward square leg for a boundary.

SIX! Bring it on! Rishabh Pant is ready to take on Jack Leach here. Floated delivery, full and outside off, Pant shimmies down the track and clobbers it behind the bowler for a biggie. The 50-run stand comes up.
Loopy delivery, full and around off, Pant drives it back to the bowler. 14 from the over!
Runs are flowing now for India. Broad angles in a shortish delivery, around middle, Pant glances it in front of square on the leg side for two. 150 comes up!
Broad hurls across a length ball close to off, Jadeja covers the line and leaves.
Identical to the last delivery, Jadeja has been patient with his leaves. Makes another one.
Slightly short this time, outside off, Ravindra Jadeja is not getting tempted at the moment. He allows it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, close to off and angling in this time, Jadeja leans back a bit, keeps his bat carefully away from the line as he leaves.
A big outswinger but the line is quite wide outside off to trouble the batter. Jadeja offers no shot.
Pant steps out but does not get to the pitch of the ball. He pushes it to the right of the bowler.
Flatter this time and on off, Pant blocks.
Really well fielded by Potts! On the pads, Pant sweeps, the man at short fine leg dives to his right and saves three for his side.
Nicely bowled! This is the one which goes on with the arm, it is on off, Jadeja blocks inside the line, it goes off the outer half towards point for one.
On middle, blocked.
Flatter and gets this one to zip through. Pant though negotiates it well as he defends.
On middle, Jadeja works it towards mid-wicket and takes one.
Pant misses out! On the pads, Pant swings, he looks to go over fine leg but misses to get hit on the pads.
Loose! This is a very wide delivery and short. Pant throws his bat at it but is beaten.
Well bowled! On off and on a length. Pant looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Around off, Pant opens the face of the bat and guides it through point. He runs the first one aggressively and returns for the second run.
FOUR! Pant gets it away this time! It is short and wide outside off with no one at point. Stokes wants Pant to go after this and Pant does but he guides it through the vacant region for a boundary.
Slightly fuller and on off, Pant pushes it to mid off.
Flatter and on off, blocked.
Tosses it up this time and on middle, Jadeja plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, this is clipped to mid-wicket.
On middle again, it is played to mid-wicket once more.
On the stumps, Jadeja defends.
Uppishly played but safe! Fuller and on middle, Jadeja chips it down to long on for one.
Angles it in from around the wicket, Jadeja is solid in defense.
Attacks the stumps again, giving nothing away. Blocked.
Angled into the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but misses.
Really well played and a good run too in the end! Shorter and on off, extra bounce. Jadeja takes one hand off the handle and guides it to point for one.
Another nice shot and more runs for India. Stokes goes fuller and on off, Pant opens the face of the bat and guides it yet again through the vacant point region for three.
Bangs it way too short, it comes slowly off the surface. Jadeja has enough time to evade it.
Yet another short one! On the body this time, it is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Flighted ball on off, defended.
Pushes it through but on the pads, Jadeja looks to nudge it on the on side but misses to get hit on the pads.
This time he eases it down to long on and gets to the other end. Pant on 49, comes on strike.
Straight to the fielder who was just brought in. On middle, Pant flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Rishabh Pant gets to his fifty in style! Crucial, crucial knock from a player who tends to always deliver when his side is in trouble. His 10th fifty in Tests. A gift, a short ball on middle for him to get there. He rocks back and pulls it through square leg. A ton is on offer here and it's been long since he has scored one. His team and Pant would love it if he gets there.
On middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket. A dot to end.
That is a good leave in the end! Length and outside off, it lands and comes back in. Jadeja leaves it, it goes closey past the off pole.
On middle, Jadeja plays it to mid on.

Confusion but safe! Shorter and on off, Jadeja guides it to point. He wants a run but is sent back. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end. Hits the stumps. The ball deflects away from the keeper to mid-wicket. Pant wants a run this time but he is sent back. This one is called a no ball for overstepping.
Yet another leave as Stokes bowls another one outside off.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Length and on off, Jadeja pushes it to covers. It's called a no ball, Ben has bowled a few in this spell.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
A bumper to end then! Short and around off, left alone. That will be TEA ON DAY 1!
Extra bounce to beat the bat! Potts starts with a beauty. Delivers it on a good length around off and gets it to angle away with some extra bounce. Rishabh Pant tries to defend but it beats his bat.

FOUR! Shot! This one is overpitched and outside off. Rishabh Pant is not going to let it go unpunished. He fully commits himself on the front foot and smashes it past the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Serves it on a length and around middle, Pant stays back to defend. It takes the inner edge and hits him on the pads.
FOUR! Moves to 61 and his strike rate is 108.9. Back of a length, around off and angling away, Pant latches onto the width and packs a punch through cover-point.
Lands it on a length and around off, Pant defends it from the back foot to covers.
Fuller in length, around middle and off, Pant pushes it softly to mid off. Steps out for a run but is sent back.
FOUR! Lovely hit from Jadeja. It's not too full but there is width outside off, Jadeja times his drive from the middle of the bat and sends it racing away to the cover fence.

Slight inward movement there, from a length around off, Jadeja defends it from the inner half of his bat. The ball rests near the popping crease and Ravindra Jadeja looks for a run. He is sent back. Anderson rushes forward to kick it onto the stumps but fails in his attempt.
On a length and outside off, going straight on, Ravindra Jadeja allows it through to the keeper.
Close to off, on a good length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja keeps his bat close to his body as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Way wide outside off, on a length and shaping away, Ravindra Jadeja leaves.
Pitches it on a length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja offers no shot.
Angling away from the batter, on a fuller length outside off, Pant brings his bat down late and pushes it to point.

FOUR! Pant is loving his shots square of the wicket on the off side. Shortish and close to off, Pant hangs deep inside the crease and slaps it through the gap for another boundary. He is taking India to safety here with his batting blitz.
Fuller this time, outside off, Pant cracks it down the ground but finds the mid off fielder.
Full again, this time in the line of the stumps, Pant defends it back close to his body.

Digs it in short, around middle, Rishabh Pant swivels and pulls it down to fine leg for a single. What happened there? It seems that Pant pulled his leg muscle while taking the run. Nothing serious though.
In the corridor outside off, Jadeja is fully committed to not playing at anything wide.
Angling in from a length around off, Rishabh Pant is solid as he defends it from the back foot towards mid on. Steps down the track but then returns.
Great delivery, a touch short and close to off, it lands and straightens as Rishabh Pant shoulders arms.

Innovation at its best! We have seen Pant doing it before against James Anderson in India. Rishabh Pant brings out the reverse-batted shot, trying to put away a length ball around off through backward point. It though takes the top edge and flies behind the slip cordon for a couple of runs.
Swing and a miss! Rishabh Pant seems to have lost focus. Tries to slog-sweep James Anderson out of the park but fails to connect. It's on a length around off, Pant swings but misses.
Gentle delivery, on a length and down the leg side, Pant tries to flick but misses.

Fuller and close to off, Pant defends it back from the inner half of his bat. Anderson moves across to his left, picks up the ball and throws it to the keeper. He is looking a bit frustrated as Pant stands there, showing no emotions.
On a length and outside off, Jadeja leaves it.
Fuller in length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja gets forward to drive but misses.
Movement off the surface this time. Around off, on a length and shapes back in, Jadeja feels for it inside the line and gets beaten.
On a length and outside off, Jadeja taps it down to cover-point for a single.
FOUR! The century stand comes up! Short in length, around leg, Rishabh Pant turns inside the crease and pulls it down to fine leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Rishabh Pant and he is doing it for India. 200 comes up! Short again from Potts, around middle and there isn't much pace or lift on this delivery. Rishabh Pant swivels and eases it via a pull shot to the fine leg fence.
Angles it in, on a length around off, Jadeja defends it to the leg side.
Jimmy lands it on a length and close to off, Jadeja presses forward and defends it to covers.
Anderson puts this one close to off and on a length, there is some late away movement on this delivery, Jadeja covers the line and safely leaves it.
Short this time, around off, Jadeja punches it off the back foot but finds point.
On a good length and outside off, shaping away, Jadeja lets it be.
Darts it on a length and around off, Jadeja comes forward and defends it to the cover region.

FOUR! Three boundaries in a row now that Potts have conceded! Pant into the 80s. Full and on middle, this is clipped stylishly through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence. Also, Pant now has 2000 Test runs for India.
Goes back to bowling length and serves it on off, Pant defends it towards covers.
Length yet again, this lands around off and angles away. Left alone.
A quick run! On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket and the batters cross ends.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! Potts is leaking runs here. He has been quite wayward in this spell of his. On the pads, Jadeja looks to flick, but it hits the pads and runs down to the fine leg fence. Potts is probably trying too hard, he seems frustrated about something.
FOUR! That has been put away with disdain! Length and on middle, Pant steps out and thumps it over the bowler's head for a boundary. He is really going after Anderson and winning the battle so far.
Angles this one into the pads, Pant looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On middle, Pant blocks it out.
Another one on the pads, Pant works it through square leg for one.
A little too straight again, Jadeja looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Slightly fuller and shaping away from outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Fortunate one! This is full and outside off, Jadeja goes after it and it flies off the outside edge down to the third man fence. This is a good counter-punch from India. Frustrating for England.
The effort ball! A loud grunt as Matthew Potts delivers it. It is outside off though and it is an easy leave.
Yet another delivery outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
Another one on the fuller side, Jadeja strokes it to mid on.
Yet another full ball, on the off pole, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
Two to end the over! Angled into the pads, this is clipped through square leg for a couple of runs.
Angled into the body, Pant works it down to fine leg and takes one.
On off, Jadeja defends.
Well fielded! Shorter and around off, Jadeja slaps it to point where the Ollie Pope dives across to his right and stops it.
Fuller and on off, Jadeja pushes it to covers.
Angled into the middle pole line, Jadeja is solid in defense.
Back of a length and on middle, Jadeja works it to mid on.
Tossed up on off, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, turning back in, this is worked through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, Jadeja defends it solidly.
On the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, defended.
Shorter and on off, Jadeja pushes it towards covers for one.

Ouch! That might have hurt! Outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone. It keeps swinging away after passing the batter. Billings dives to his left, it hits his glove and then goes on to strike Joe Root on his left shin. Smiles everywhere.
Shorter and on middle, Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, yet another easy leave.
FOUR LEG BYES! Another boundary in that fine leg region! On the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but misses, it hits the pads and rolls down to the fine leg fence.
Goes short and outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Another one outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Up and over! Lots of real estate there. Pant into the 90s. Steps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and hits it with the turn to wide long on for a boundary.

FOUR! Thumped down the ground this time! Pant has fallen down on the ground, that is how hard he swung his bat at this delivery. Steps out again, he gets to the pitch of it and swings, it goes over the bowler's head for a boundary. Another one will see him get to his ton.
A single now! Sensible stuff! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Jadeja now takes one as this is eased down to long on.
Pant keeps strike as he moves to 98! On the pads, this is swept down to the deep backward square leg fielder for one.

HUNDRED FOR PANT! Outstanding running between the wicket, the desperation to get to that ton was shown there! Risked it all but in the end, made it in with a dive. What an innings! Absolutely brilliant. Came out to bat when India were 3 down for not a lot but his knock and his partnership with Jadeja is taking India to a good first innings score. Gets there with a pull shot as it is bowled short and on his body. It goes towards fine leg. They take one. The fielder runs to his left, and collects the ball, Pant wants the second and completes it as a weak throw comes to the keeper. Takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause. Really well deserved. A Test century off 89 balls, Harsha Bhogle (on air) informs that this is the fastest by an Indian wicketkeeper. Take a bow, young man!
Goes short again, on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
FOUR! More runs! This is very frustrating for the hosts! Around off and on a length, this is guided down to third man for a boundary. India nearing 250 now.

Fifty for Jadeja and he does his trademark sword celebration! Really good knock from him too. He understood his role, was happy to play second fiddle to Pant and has got the reward. He would want to get to three figures too. This is fuller and on middle, this is pushed wide of mid on for one.
Bangs it short and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Back of a length, on middle. Jadeja works it to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Jadeja pushes it gently to covers for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! A shorter-length delivery on middle. Pant waits for it and clips it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Beaten! Slower in the air and around off. Pant looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angles it into leg. Pant paddles it to short fine leg. The fielder dives and stops it. A single taken.
On the shorter side on middle. Jadeja works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, Jadeja sweeps it wide of short fine leg for a single.
NO BALL! Back of a length and down the leg side. Jadeja ducks and lets it go. Stokes has overstepped here.
Short ball on middle. Jadeja lets it go as it is too high.
Another bouncer on middle. Jadeja ducks under it.
Short ball stuff continues, on off. Jadeja pulls it to deepish mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Jadeja blocks it out.
NO BALL! Another bouncer from Stokes and Jadeja ducks under it. Stokes continues to overstep as well.
Stokes with a bouncer angling into leg. Jadeja ducks under it.

FOUR BYES! This is quite wayward stuff from the English skipper! Stokes with a short delivery and it is way down the leg side. Jadeja lets it go and Billings behind the stumps has no chance as well and it is boundary for India!
Taps it down to point for a run.
Short and on middle, pulled behind square leg for a single.
FOUR! Boundaries continue to flow. Short and around middle, Pant bends his back knee and powers his sweep shot through square leg for a boundary.
SIX! Pant continues to take Leach to the cleaners. Loopy and full, landing outside off, Pant races down the track and towers it over long on for a biggie.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! England are losing the plot here. Flatter and a touch shorter on middle, Pant helps it behind square leg. The fielder fires a wild throw at the keeper's end, away from Billings, as it races to the deep cover fence.

SIX! Colossal hit! That trademark one-handed maximum from Rishabh Pant. Flighted delivery, around off, Rishabh Pant is again down the track as he hoists it over long on. His bottom hand comes off the handle but it has no impact on the shot. 22 from the over!
Back of a length, around middle and leg, Ravindra Jadeja defends it down on the leg side.
Short in length and outside off, Jadeja drops his wrists and allows it through to the keeper.
Short in length but down the leg side, Jadeja leaves.
Short and on middle, Jadeja hangs on the back foot and pulls it through square leg for a single. Another overstepping, 9th no ball bowled by England now.
Sliding down the leg side, it's nudged down to fine leg for a run.
Bouncer around off, Jadeja crouches and sways away from the line of fire.
Another bouncer and again Jadeja ducks.
Flighted and full, wide outside off, Pant walks down the track and drives it to wide mid off for a single.
Slower through the air, Jadeja takes it on the full and bunts it to mid off for one.
Tossed up and outside off, Pant LEAVES.
SIX! Just one leave and the next one is sent to the fence. Flighted and outside off, Pant latches onto the width and hammers it over extra cover.
A low full toss on off, Pant forces it down to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! What was that? Root bowls a bouncer, around middle, Pant somehow manages to connect with his pull shot and sends it to the fine leg fence.

FOUR! England seems to have given up and waiting for the close of play. Short and around middle, Ravindra Jadeja turns and pulls it disdainfully to the deep mid-wicket fence. The double-century stand comes up!
Bouncer. Jadeja ducks.
Short in length and outside off, shaping away, Jadeja sways away.
Stokes arrows in a length ball, around middle, Jadeja defends it from the back foot.
Bumper outside off, Jadeja sits underneath it.
Around off, on a length, Jadeja plays it with soft hands to covers and picks up a single.
Loopy delivery, full and outside off, Jadeja lunges and defends it back from the inner half of his bat.
Short this time, outside off, Ravindra Jadeja goes on the back foot and cuts it to deep point for a couple of runs.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Jadeja presses forward and pushes it to covers.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A touch short and around off, Jadeja rocks on the back foot and cuts it past Broad at backward point for a boundary. Moves to 67!
Leans forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.
Some extra bounce from a shortish length around off, Pant hangs back to glance but fails to connect well. It strikes him on the gloves and Pant has hurt his fingers.
Short again but down the leg side, Pant tries to glance once more but misses.
A half-tracker again, on middle, Pant pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Almost drags it on. Back of a length, around off, Jadeja defends it from the inside half of his blade. The ball drops in front of the stumps and rolls behind. They steal a run.
Stokes continues to overstep. A short delivery down the leg side and it has been pulled to fine leg for one.
Shortish and around off, some steep bounce there, Jadeja initially looks to duck but then fends it away safely to backward point.
Stokes continues to be short, outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.

SIX! This one falls right on the boundary line. Fuller and around off, Pant walks down the track and muscles it over the bowler's head. It lands flush on the rope and the umpire signals for a maximum after getting it checked upstairs.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! Soft dismissal for Rishabh Pant. The crowd goes Rooooooooo... and then stands to applaud this swashbuckling knock from Pant. Slower through the air, full and outside off, turning away a bit as well. Rishabh Pant goes down on one knee for a big slog sweep over mid-wicket to bring his 150 in style but only manages a thick outside edge. Zak Crawley is alert and takes the catch safely. Pant returns with his bat raised.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Joe Root

Commentary: Floated delivery, dipping in full around off, Thakur digs it out back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker, short as well, around off, Thakur defends it from the back foot.
Fires it in flat, around off, Shardul defends it back.
Loopy and full, around off, Thakur wristily drives it through covers and opens his account with a single. End of a successful over for England, after ages.
Digs it in short, around leg, Shardul Thakur ducks.
Around off, on a good length, Thakur defends it from the back foot.
Bumper around leg, Thakur sits underneath it easily.
Slightly short and on off, Thakur defends it back from the crease. Another overstepping from Stokes.
Bowls a bouncer on middle and leg, Shardul Thakur doesn't want to do anything fancy at the moment.
Goes full this time, around off, Shardul Thakur blocks it solidly to the off side.
Fraction short and on off, Shardul Thakur is on his toes as he defends it down on the leg side. Another no ball. Stokes cannot believe it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The extra ball gifts Stokes a wicket. A well-directed short ball, around off and it shoots up off the surface. Shardul Thakur is surprised by the extra bounce, tries to sway away but it clips his gloves and goes to the keeper. Sam Billings takes a diving catch to his right and England get their second wicket in the session.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Angles it in, on a length, Jadeja defends it from the back foot.
Back of a length, around middle, Jadeja is on his toes as he plays it down to square leg.
Jadeja goes on his toes to this short ball and blocks it down.
Angling down the leg side, Jadeja flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Shortish and on middle, Shami stands back and defends it on the leg side.
On a length and around off, Shami goes on the back foot and defends it from the inner half of his blade.
Lands on a length, around off. Jadeja defends it towards the off side.
Short ball on middle. Jadeja pulls it firmly to deep mid-wicket. He finds the fielder there and denies a single.
No single taken again! Short and wide outside off. Jadeja cuts it to the deep point fielder.
Back of a length, around off. Jadeja punches it through covers and takes a single this time.
Stokes goes short and it is angling into leg. Shami pulls but mistimes it to backward square leg.

An appeal for a caught behind! The umpire is not interested though and Stokes take a review! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. So the original decision stays. Coming to the ball - It is short and down the leg side. Shami looks to clip it away fine but misses. Billing behind the stumps catches the ball moving to his left. There is an appeal for a caught behind but the replays confirm that there is no bat involved.

Dropped! But a great attempt. Shortish and angling down the leg side, Jadeja tries to flick but gets a thin inside edge. It then brushes his thigh pad and goes behind. Sam Billings dives across to his right but only manages to deflect it towards fine leg. Two runs.
Short and outside off, played down to point.
Back of a length, around off and straightening a touch, Jadeja pushes at it and misses.
Gets forward and pushes a length ball in the gap at covers. Takes a single.
Potts goes short to Shami as well. Around off, Shami is on his toes as he defends it to the off side.
Short and on off, Shami pulls nicely but finds Anderson at mid-wicket.
A gentle delivery from Stokes, on a length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja leaves it untouched.
Around middle, on a good length, Jadeja helps it through square leg. No run taken.
Shortish and on off, Ravindra Jadeja defends it from the back foot.
Fuller and around middle, Jadeja eases it down through mid on for a run.
Shami goes fishing and nearly edges it behind. Short and wide outside off, Shami flashes his bat at it and misses.
A nice bumper, close to off and shooting off the surface, Shami sways away at the last moment.
FOUR! Shot! Fuller in length, around middle and leg, Jadeja whips it across the line and finds the gap at mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off, Jadeja plays late and chops it down to gully. He sets off for a run and then returns.

FIVE RUNS! Around middle, on a good length, staying down too, Jadeja helps it to square leg and steals a single. The fielder misses his shy at the striker's end. It beats the two back-up fielders and races away to the fence.
In the channel outside off, it's left alone with ease by Shami.
Potts spears it in, full and around off, Shami defends it to mid on.
Serves it on a good length and around off, Mohammad Shami jumps behind the line of the delivery and blocks it to the off side. That's it. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Ben Stokes begins from 'round the wicket angle and serves a length delivery outside off, Ravindra Jadeja wants to be watchful at the start and makes a leave.
This one is angled in the line of the off stump, Jadeja has to play at it and he pushes it away towards gully-point.
Stokes goes fuller but the line is too straight, Jadeja works it to the left of long on and he calls for two. Shami is a bit late in responding for the second run and Jadeja aborts the idea.
Stokes switches to over the wicket and delivers a shortish ball around off, Shami jumps and defends it towards backward point. Jadeja is keen to get back on strike but there is no run available.
Back of a length, around off, Shami is on his toes and plays it down to backward point.
Shortish again, around off, Shami stays on the back foot and plays it down safely to point.

SHOUT FOR AN LBW! Not given and England don't review. Matthew Potts steams in from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja fails to flick and is rapped on the pads. They appeal but that seems to be going down the leg side.
Shortish and around off, Jadeja defends it from the back foot.
Angling into the batter from around off, on a good length, Jadeja helps it towards mid-wicket and doesn't try for the single.
Picks a run on the fourth ball. Back of a length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja runs it down to third man.
Digs it in short, around middle and leg, Shami gets on top of the bounce and eases his pull shot nicely to deep backward square leg. He is a very capable batter and Jadeja can trust him more.
Shortish and on middle, jumping onto the batter a bit, Shami nicely controls the extra bounce and plays it down towards mid-wicket.
Too full in length and around leg, Jadeja helps it through mid-wicket. Takes no run.
Angling away, outside off, it's played down to third man but again no run is attempted.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it back solidly.
Beaten! Stokes delivers a gentle outswinger, landing on a fuller length around off, Ravindra Jadeja tries to play straight but is beaten by the movement.
Slanting down the leg side, Jadeja picks it off his pads and works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Back of a length, around off and shaping away, Shami stands back, gets slightly squared up as he guides it towards point.
Fuller in length around off, Jadeja flicks it through mid-wicket and takes a single. He is shaking his head. Perhaps the calculation went wrong and now Shami will have five balls to face.
Short in length, around off, Shami stays deep inside the crease and plays a controlled pull shot to square leg.

FOUR! Shami finds the fence! He loves playing his pull shots. Picks the length early, it's short and right in the zone for him. He rides the bounce and pulls it in the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Lovely! These shots will help Shami in gaining Jadeja's confidence. Short in length again, this time outside off, Shami uses the pace of the bowler and steers it through point for a boundary.
Digs it in short, around middle, Shami top-edges his pull shot down to fine leg and Jadeja is ready to pick up a run on the penultimate ball.
Potts continues to serve short balls, outside off, Jadeja mistimes his pull shot to mid on. 10 from the over.
Fraction short and around middle, Shami glances it behind square leg and takes a single.

EDGY FOUR! Nothing going England's way and Stokes has his hands on his head. Short in length and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja goes on his toes and tries to control the extra bounce as he intends to play it through point. But the ball takes the outside edge and flies past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Fuller in length and outside off, Jadeja pushes it through covers and rotates the strike.

FOUR! Shami is certainly growing in confidence. Stokes bangs it in short, around middle, Shami goes for the pull shot but takes his eyes off this time. Still, the connection is enough to take the ball towards long leg for a boundary.
Bouncer around leg, Mohammad Shami shapes up to play the pull shot but then doesn't go through with it.
Shortish and around middle, Shami goes on the back foot and gently pushes it through mid on. They take a run and Shami has a smile on his face.
Short and down the leg side, Shami tries to pull but misses.
A half-tracker on middle, Shami pulls and keeps it all along the ground. It goes to deep backward square leg and they take a single.
In the channel outside off, a rare good-length delivery, Jadeja allows it through.
Another delivery on a length outside off, angling in a bit, Ravindra Jadeja stands back to guard his stumps and shoulders arms.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Matthew Potts delivers it short and around off, Ravindra Jadeja stands back to slap it through the line but it takes a thick outside edge and flies towards the slip cordon. Zak Crawley reacts from second slip, Joe Root from first slip, the former doesn't get any hand but the latter fingertips it behind for a boundary.

FOUR! CENTURY FOR RAVINDRA JADEJA! His third in Test cricket and he is looking very relieved. Jadeja is turning out to be the crisis man for India. The limelight has been mostly on Rishabh Pant but Jadeja has also been delivering the goods with the bat on a consistent basis. The Indian dressing room is on its feet as 'Sir' does his trademark sword celebration. He reaches there by smashing a short ball through cover-point for a boundary.
Shortish and on middle, Shami defends it down from the back foot.
Short and wide outside off, Shami flashes his bat at it but misses.
Short again, on middle, a controlled pull shot towards square leg. Shami has played all the short balls quite well.

OUT! STRAIGHT TO THIRD MAN! The short-ball ploy eventually works for England. Broad serves it outside off, Mohammad Shami camps back and tries to ramp it over third man. The connection though is not enough to beat Jack Leach near the fence who takes a simple catch moving across to his left. Wicket number 550 in Test cricket for Stuart Broad and he flashes a smile. England have broken the frustrating 48-run stand and would look to pick the last two wickets quickly.
Howout: c Jack Leach b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Short and outside off, Bumrah decides to leave but is late in taking his bat away. It deflects off the willow to third man.

SAVES SIX RUNS! Broad bangs it short and on middle, Jasprit Bumrah takes on the challenge and pulls it off the top edge to fine leg. Zak Crawley catches it at the edge of the boundary line but then finds himself falling on the rope. He immediately releases it. The third umpire gets involved and the replays find that it's a fantastic effort.
Full in length and outside off, Jadeja leaves.
Fuller again, around middle and leg, Ravindra Jadeja flicks it through square leg and rushes back for the second run.
Fuller around off, Jadeja tries to work it straight but it takes the inner half to deep mid-wicket. No run is taken.
On a length and down the leg side, Jadeja misses out on tickling it to fine leg.
On the pads, this time it's flicked to the right if fine leg and he walks to complete a single.
Fuller and around off, angling in, Jasprit Bumrah defends it solidly to the off side.
This one jags back into the left-hander, from a length around off, Jadeja closes the face of his bat and helps it to square leg.
Fuller in length around off, angling in, Jadeja cracks it down the ground but finds long on. No run is taken.
Play and a miss! Shortish and around middle, angling in, Ravindra Jadeja steps back and advances down the track to cut it through the line but misses.
Short again, outside off, this time Jadeja stays put and cuts it down to deep backward point. Takes a single. Two balls to negotiate for the Indian skipper.
Fuller in length, around middle, Bumrah flicks it in front of square on the leg side. No run is taken.
Fullish and on middle, Bumrah defends it watchfully to end the over safely.
Back of a length and outside off, Jadeja stands back and steers it down to third man.

OUT! BOWLED! Anderson has a 4-fer and it ends the fantastic knock of Ravindra Jadeja. It's served on a length around middle, perhaps shaping in a bit, Jadeja tries to heave it across the line, over mid-wicket but misses and finds his stumps shattered. The crowd is on its feet as Jadeja returns. Can India get to 400 now?
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: Around off, on a length, Siraj defends it from the back foot.
Short and around leg, Siraj goes on his toes and helps it behind square leg for a single.
Lands it on a length around middle, getting it to straighten, Bumrah stands on the back foot and defends it in front of himself.

A gentle delivery, full and angling down, Bumrah tries to flick but then pulls his bat back. It goes off his pads to fine leg and they cross. The umpire feels that he was offering a shot and signals a leg bye.

FOUR! Just away from the outstretched hands of Zak Crawley. Perhaps clipped his fingers a bit. Short and around middle, Bumrah top-edges his pull shot down to fine leg. Crawley moves across to his left, puts a sliding effort to catch it but in vain.
FIVE WIDES! India will take these extras gleefully. Stuart Broad digs it in short and it goes over the batter and the leaping keeper for a boundary.

SIX! And it's no ball also for overstepping. Precious runs for India. Short again, around middle, Jasprit Bumrah attempts to wheel another pull shot but it takes the top edge and flies all the way over fine leg.

FOUR! India are nearing 400 now. The idea from Stuart Broad was right but not the execution. Aims for a yorker but it turns out to be a full toss on off, Bumrah smacks it down to long on for a boundary.

FOUR! 400 COMES UP FOR INDIA! Bumrah is turning out to be the master of edges. This one is on a length and around off, Jasprit Bumrah attempts for a big heave over the leg side but it takes the inner edge, beats the stumps and speeds away to the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Bumrah has sent another one to the fence. Back of a length, around leg, Jasprit Bumrah smashes it across the line, falls in the process but still finds the fence in front of square leg.

SIX! 34 off the over already with one more ball to go. Broad is being reminded of Yuvraj Singh here. Short again, around leg, Jasprit Bumrah turns inside the crease and smokes it over fine leg for a maximum.

AND BUMRAH WILL KEEP STRIKE! The crowd roars. Smart batting from the skipper. Broad bowls a yorker for once, around off, Bumrah digs it out on the pitch and rushes across to the other end. Siraj responds and puts in a dive as Broad scores a direct hit at the striker's end. It's referred upstairs for a run out but the replays find Siraj safe. 35 from the over - the most expensive over in the history of Test cricket. Whoa!
Beamer! A high full toss on middle, Bumrah helps it towards mid-wicket and crosses. It's called a no ball.
Back of a length, around off, Siraj stands back and swings his bat at it but fails to connect.
Swing and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Siraj throws his bat it but fails to connect.
Fuller and around off, Mohammad Shami pushes it down to mid off and takes a single.
Short in length and outside off, Bumrah plays late at it and deflects it down to third man for a run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Yet another fifer for James Anderson. Back of a length, around off, Mohammed Siraj rocks back and tries to power it across the line. But it flies off the toe end of the bat and Stuart Broad moves swiftly across to his right from mid off to take the skier safely. India are all out for 416!
Howout: c Stuart Broad b James Anderson

Commentary: Starts off with a short of a length delivery, on off. Alex Lees goes on the back foot and keeps it out.

Half an appeal for LBW but it is not given! Jasprit Bumrah goes fuller and lands it around the leg stump. The ball shapes in and Alex Lees is caught rooted to the crease. The ball pings him on the pads and the fielding side goes up in unision. The umpire shakes his head, probably pitching outside leg.
Alex Lees is underway! This is on the pads again and this time, Lees is able to clip it through square leg for a couple of runs. England are up and running.
Pulls back the length a touch and slants this one across the left-hander. Alex Lees makes a comfortable leave.
Almost an action replay of the previous delivery. Length, around off and shaping away, no shot offered by Lees.
Touch fuller this time but keeps it around the off stump. The ball shapes away from the left-hander and Lees just shoulders his arms. Two runs then off the opening over.
Starts off with a full delivery, in that corridor around the off pole. Zak Crawley watches it closely and lets it through to the keeper.
Big outswinger this time. On a good length, outside off and moving further away. Zak Crawley isn't one bit interested in playing at that one.
Much better from Shami! Right around the top of off, touching 140 clicks. Crawley solidly keeps it out.
Leg bye! Goes full this time and drifts onto the pads, Crawley looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads and rolls towards square leg. The batters scamper through for a leg bye.

EDGED AND FOUR! A nervy moment early on for Alex Lees but he survives. Mohammad Shami comes from around the wicket and has an extra slip in place. Shami though angles this one in on a good length and into off stump. Lees tries to play it as late as possible but ends up getting an inside edge that goes past the stumps and runs away into the fine leg fence.
On a fuller length, close to the off pole and shaping away. Lees makes a watchful leave.
This is pitched up and just shaping away a touch from middle stump. Crawley presses forward to defend it out.
Short of a length and wide of the off pole, Crawley shoulders arms at that one. No ball called for overstepping.
Full and angling in on the pads, Crawley works it towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Lovely way to get off the mark from Zak Crawley. Bumrah keeps it full but it's just a bit too straight. Crawley hangs back and just wrists it with great timing through the sqaure leg region for a boundary.

Edged and away! Bumrah angles this one into middle and off but the ball nips away. Crawley plays at it with soft hands but gets an outside edge that goes down and to the right of the man at third slip. Shubman Gill over there gets a hand on it which takes some pace off it. Two runs taken.
Good length, on off. This is solidly blocked off by Crawley.
Yet another no ball, second of the over! Length again but on the pads, Crawley tucks it away towards square leg for an easy single.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Jasprit Bumrah gets the rub of the green with the extra delivery and sends Alex Lees packing! Bumrah switches to around the wicket and bowls it on a fuller length, angling in from around off. The ball doesn't swing much and just goes on with the angle. Lees though camps back and looks to play it late. His feet don't move and the ball goes off the pads and castles into the stumps. England's opening woes continue and India have the early breakthrough. England trail by 400 runs.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: FOUR BYES! What a delivery to begin proceedings here! Mohammad Shami starts off with a slightly back-of-a-length delivery on off and gets the ball to shape away. Massive movement as it beats the batter as well as the keeper to run away for four extra runs!

A bit of a mix-up but no damage is done! Goes full this time outside off, Zak Crawley drives this firmly towards backward point where there is a half stop. Both batters set off for a run before Crawley sends his partner back. Ollie Pope was halfway down the track but has enough time to get back.
Full once again and angling into the pads, Zak Crawley tries to work this leg side but gets a leading edge towards covers for a brace.
Good-length delivery pitching on the off stump line. Zak Crawley knocks this towards mid on.
Angling down leg once more and a fraction full, Zak Crawley tries to flick this but misses and gets a single to short fine leg with the help of his pads.

FOUR! Off the mark in style! Shami decides to test the batter with a short deliver straight up but Ollie Pope is up to the task. Pulls this wide of the deep square leg fielder to start with a boundary!

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Jasprit Bumrah with a double-strike and Zak Crawley is sent packing! Bumrah goes fuller and pushes it a bit outside off. The ball is shaping away and Crawley just gets suckered into playing the cover-drive. The ball goes off the outside edge and it's an easy catch for Shubman Gill at third slip. Both English openers have fallen prey to the Indian skipper early on and Bumrah will now be on a hat-trick.
Howout: c Shubman Gill b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: What a delivery! Serves it full on off, with a bit of away movement. Root tries to play at it but it gets past his outside edge. No hat-trick!

Edged but safe! On a length and at the stumps, the ball straightens after pitching as well. Root looks to work it onto the leg side but gets a leading edge past the cover-point fielder and gets off the mark with a brace.
Bowls it on a length around off, the ball goes past the outside edge of Root's willow yet again.
Good length delivery, angling in. Root plays a solid defense back to the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Root lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Mohammad Shami gets the ball to pitch on the off stump line off a good length. Ollie Pope works this towards square leg for a single. Joe Root looks for a second but is sent back by Ollie Pope.
Good delivery from Mohammad Shami as this one shapes away outside off on a good length. Joe Root is watchful and lets this one through.
Length delivery and outside off. Joe Root defends this towards cover.
Good-length delivery angling in from outside off stump. Joe Root gets onto his front foot and defends solidly.
Almost gets an inside edge onto his stumps here! Outside the off-stump line on a good length. The ball shapes back in and gets an inside edge as Joe Root tries to defend this off his back foot.
Straighter this time landing on a good length. Joe Root holds his bat upright and plays it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Bumrah goes full and outside off, this one holds its line. Pope tries to play at it but gets beaten and it goes past his outside edge.
Goes full again on off, angling in. Pope blocks it off well this time.
Good length delivery around the off stump, Pope moves across and pushes it towards point for a single.
FOUR! Great start by England after the interruption. Bumrah starts with a full delivery on the off, Root leans forward and drives it through the mid off region for a boundary.
Serves it on a length around leg, moving away, Root leaves it alone.
Bowls it full and around off stump, Root pushes this one of his back foot to the off side.
Fuller in length, on the fourth stump line and shaping away a touch. Ollie Pope makes a watchful leave.
Keeps it around the off stump and just pulls back the length a touch. Pope makes yet another leave.
On a good length this time, outside off. Pope goes deep in his crease and dabs it down with soft hands towards the gully region.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shorter in length and a bit of width on offer as well. Ollie Pope just helps it on its way wide of the fielder at gully for a boundary.
Shami goes full again, around off and shaping away. Pope looks to cover drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Keeps it on a fuller length and serves it wider, Pope doesn't fall for the dangled carrot and lets it safely through to the keeper.
Length, around the top of off. Root stays inside the crease and nudges it towards point.
Full and wide, Root makes the leave as the ball swings away after leaving the batter. No ball called for overstepping.
Full and straight, punched firmly but it is cut off by the fielder at silly mid on.
Pitched up again, around middle. Root drives on the up but straight to the man at silly mid on.
Full and around off, at 142 clicks. Joe Root pushes it to the left of the man at short extra cover for a quick single.
On a length, angling into middle and leg. Pope has a slight shuffle across the off stump but fails to work it behind square on the leg side.
Short of a good length and outside off, the ball shoots up nicely off the surface. Ollie Pope gets behind it and does well to keep it down on the off side.
Fuller and around off, Root blocks it out.

Half an appeal but probably a bit too high that one. On a perfect length, around off and this one comes back in off the surface. Joe Root gets caught on the crease and gets pegged back as he is pinged on the pads. The replay confirms that the ball was going well over the middle stump.
Back of a length, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time and a bit closer to the off pole. Joe Root puts out a big stride and watches the ball go past him, into the keeper's mitts.
Wants the second but won't get it. Back of a length, around middle and leg, Root works it off his hips past backward square leg for a single.
Pacy delivery, around 140 clicks, fuller and just zipping off the surface. Ollie Pope doesn't play at it.
Good-length delivery pitching outside off, angling in. Joe Root leaves this one alone.
Fraction shorter and closer to the stumps, Joe Root fends this off towards point.
Jasprit Bumrah goes full and angles it in from outside off. Joe Root plays this with soft hands towards cover and rushes across for a single.

Nips back in sharply from outside off. Jasprit Bumrah bowls this on a good length and Ollie Pope comes across the stumps to play this but gets beaten. The ball thumps against his pads but outside the line of the stumps.
Full this time angling into the stumps, Ollie Pope defends this back towards the bowler.
NO BALL! Length ball outside off stump which stays low and bounces just in front of Rishabh Pant as Ollie Pope lets it go.

OUT! TAKEN! Deja vu! At this point, Jasprit Bumrah might just deliberately bowl no balls on the final delivery of the over just to pick up a wicket off the next delivery! Full and wide this time, Ollie Pope looks to cover drive but does so away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge and flies to the right of Shreyas Iyer at second slip and he takes a sharp catch. The skipper has three and England in a bit of a fix here as they still trail by 372 runs.
Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Bowls it full on the off, angling in, Root blocks it off to the leg side.
Serves it on a good-length, shaping in. Root moves across to play at it but gets hit on his body.
Bowls it on a length and around middle and leg, Root flicks it off his back foot towards deep sqaure leg for a single.
On a length and outside off, Bairstow leaves it alone.
A bit fuller and outside off again, Bairstow still offers no shot at it.
Serves it on a length outside off, Bairstow pushes this one off his back foot but finds the fielder at short covers.
On a length, around the fifth stump line. Root leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, slanted in from around off. Root hangs back and pushes it out towards backward point.
A touch fuller and around off, Root punches it off the front foot and through covers for a couple of runs.
Good-length delivery outside off, Joe Root goes back in his crease and punches this through point for a brace.
