FOUR! That is a lucky boundary for Joe Root! Jasprit Bumrah goes a fraction fuller and angles it into the pads from outside off. He tries to work this one leg side but gets and leading-edge through the gap between point and cover for four runs! Jasprit Bumrah asking some nice questions here!
On a good length outside off. There is good shape on the ball and Joe Root raises his hands and lets it through.
Starts with a short delivery on off, Bairstow pulls it towards the deep square leg region and picks up a brace. He is off the mark!
CLOSE! Shami bowls it full outside off, shaping away. Bairstow drives at it but gets an outside edge. Luckily for him it did not carry to the man at third slip.
On a length and on middle, Bairstow plays a solid defense.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Bowls it full and on middle, Bairstow blocks it down the pitch.
Good-Length delivery outside off, shaping away. Bairstow lets it go to the keeper.

Edged again but safe again. This one lands on a length outside off, angling in. Bairstow tries to push it but the extra bounce gets the handle of his bat and the ball falls short of the gully fielder.
Mohammed Siraj starts off with a full delivery on off, Joe Root flicks this straight to the square leg fielder.
Straying in line this time as he bowls this angling down leg side from a good length. Joe Root flicks this to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow gets his first boundary in typical style! Mohammed Siraj is slightly short and in line with the stumps. Sits up nicely for him to pull this wide of square leg for four runs!
Full delivery angling into the pads once again, Jonny Bairstow misses out on his flick as it finds the square leg fielder.
Much better length from Mohammed Siraj outside off stump. Jonny Bairstow lets this one go through casually.
Outside off stump line on a good length. Jonny Bairstow works this towards the gully fielder. 5 runs from Mohammed Siraj's first over.
Serves it on a length around off, shaping away. Root throws his bat at it and the ball goes just past the outside edge.
Loose, very loose from Root. He needs to regain his focus here. Shami begins with a tempter outside off, full and outside off, Joe Root aims for a booming drive, away from his body and gets beaten.

FOUR! Edgy from Root. Seems Joe Root has taken a leaf out of Rishabh Pant's book - Attack is the best form of defense! Chases a full ball again, outside off and slices his drive through backward point for a boundary.
That's more like Root. Lets the ball to come to him and offers a dead straight bat in defense.

Serves it on a length and around off, Joe Root stays on the back foot and pushes it away to cover-point. He takes a step forward and Jonny Bairstow responds by taking quite a few steps but only to be sent back.

FOUR! In full control on this occasion. Shami delivers it in the zone outside off, Joe Root unfurls a lovely drive through the gap at covers and picks up a boundary. He is trying to be positive and was seen using his feet to play this shot.
Starts by angling in a length ball around off, Bairstow goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Bumrah keeps angling in a length ball, around off again, Jonny is content with defending it down from the back foot.
Extra bounce this time. It's on a length and around off, jagging back in, Jonny Bairstow fails to defend and is hit on the back thigh.

HUGE SHOUT FOR AN LBW! The umpire shakes his head. Bumrah discusses with his keeper and is heard saying - 'height hai!' Meaning it's too high. Bumrah serves it on a length and lands it around off, this one lands and nips back in, Bairstow fails to work it around and is hit high on the pads.
Movement off the deck again. Bairstow tries to play at it, through the line but gets an inside edge onto the pads. A no ball is called.
Fullish this time, around middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow tries to flick but closes the face of his bat early. It take a soft leading edge and rolls towards mid on.
Too full and around off, Bairstow is failing to pick the variation. Tries to play across the line but it takes the inner edge and rolls through square leg for a couple.
Delivers it on a length and just outside off, Root stays back to cover the line and shoulders arms.
Shami pitches it up this time, around off, Root drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Around off, on a length, Root gets firmly behind the line and blocks it to covers.

Excellent shot! Shami gets a little bit too straight with his line, Root leans across and flicks it beautifully off his pads. Finds the gap at mid-wicket and by the time, Jasprit Bumrah chases it down and returns it back in play, the batters take three runs.
Fuller and closer to off, Jonny Bairstow pushes it wristily to covers.

Nicely played in the end! Shami goes wide of the crease and serves it a bit short outside off, Jonny decides to play the horizontal bat shot but doesn't give it the full swing of his bat. With a restricted wristwork, he places it past the mid-wicket fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Beaten all ends up! Jasprit Bumrah angles in a length ball around off and gets it to hold its line. Joe Root stays back, pushes inside the line and misses.
Identical to the last delivery, a touch fuller though, Joe stays back and shoulders arms.
Back of a length outside off, Root goes on the back foot and plays it down to the right of Ravindra Jadeja at point and picks up a single.
Fullish and around off, Jonny brings down a straight blade and forces it towards mid on.
Hurls across a length ball, close to off and just straightening a shade, Jonny Bairstow lifts his bat and lets it be.
Terrific delivery and equally well played by Jonny. Jasprit Bumrah goes for a toe-crushing yorker, and nails it as well, but Bairstow is alert and digs it out safely.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Root tries to flick but misses. Pant dives across to his left and collects the ball.
Better line this time. Around middle and on a good length, Root stays on the back foot and blocks it down safely.
Disciplined line, that's what Shami should be aiming for at the moment. Delivers it around off, angling in, Root is sound in his defense from the back foot.
A hint of away movement, from a good length around off, Root gets forward and defends it with an angled bat to point.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. The impact looked to be outside off and it was too high as well. Shami brings out the variation and serves an inswinger as a follow-up delivery. It's around off, Root steps down and tries to work it around but misses. He is hit high on the pads and the umpire turns down the appeal easily.
Back of a length, around off, Root punches it off his back foot to point. Maiden, first from India in this innings!
Jasprit Bumrah angles this one in from outside off as it lands on a good length. Jonny Bairstow fends this towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery once again in line with the stumps. Jonny Bairstow defends this back to the bowler.
Jasprit Bumrah is looking in good rhythm as he bowls this on a good length just outside off again. Jonny Bairstow knocks this towards mid off.
Fourth dot ball in a row as the length is good and on off. Jonny Bairstow though continues to be solid in defense.
Bowls a fuller delivery angling into the pads, Jonny Bairstow gets his bat down and works this towards mid on.
Goes wide from off stump on a good length. Jonny Bairstow finally does not have to play at one. Maiden over for Jasprit Bumrah as well, his first!
BEAUTY! Root is cut in half there. He attempts to play a drive to a delivery cutting back into him. The ball beats the inside edge by a whisker as it travels to the keeper.
This one lands on middle, angling in. Root tries to flick it but gets hit on the gloves due to the extra bounce.
Beaten again. Shami goes full and outside off, Root tries to cut it but misses it. completely. Shami is causing all sorts of trouble.

Huge shout for LBW! Not given. It has been reviewed though at the last second by Jasprit Bumrah. Coming to the delivery - Mohammad Shami just pulls back the length a touch and angles it in from outside off. Joe Root gets outside the crease and shuffles across looking to work it onto the leg side but misses. Root gets hit on the pads but the appeal is not entertained. DRS time! UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and Ball Tracking confirms that the ball was going over the stumps.

LEG BYE! Shami bowls it on a length around middle, nips back in sharply. Root misses it again and it hits his pads and goes to fine leg. They pick up a single. Joe Root will be happy to get off strike.
This one lands on a length outside off, and holds its line a bit. Bairstow tries to push at it but gets beaten.
Mohammed Siraj starts off well this time around. A good-length delivery angling in from outside off. Joe Root gets behind the line of the ball and fends it towards the off side.
On a good length but wide from the off stump. Joe Root slashes at it as it goes through for the keeper to collect.
Good shape on this delivery but still wide from the stumps. Joe Root leaves this one alone.
Pulls the length back slightly, and delivers this outside off. Joe Root goes for the cross-batted shot once again but gets a bottom edge that goes on the bounce to Rishabh Pant.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off and angling in, Joe Root strides forward and then lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Huge, huge moment in the game and Mohammed Siraj has got the big fish! Siraj goes a bit short and angles it in from wide of the crease. The ball pitches outside off and keeps following the batter with extra bounce. Joe Root is deep in his crease and leans back, trying to perhaps guide it over the slip cordon. The delivery is too close for comfort and the ball takes the bottom edge. Rishabh Pant takes a simple catch behind the sticks and India have the breakthrough. England trail by 338 runs.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Ouch, that would have hurt! Shami serves it on a good length, and gets some steep bounce there, Bairstow looks to defend it from the back foot but gets hit on his gloves. He has called for the physio.
Bowls it full and on middle, Bairstow blocks it out.

CLOSE! That was a brilliant delivery by Shami. Bowls it on a length just outside off, swinging in a long way. Bairstow lets it through to the keeper but it's not far from hitting the off pole. Everyone is surprised. Jonny is a lucky man!
Goes full and on off, Bairstow plays a front foot defense but the ball hits the inner edge and rolls towards square leg. They take a single.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Mohammad Shami with a peach of delivery but unfortunately for Shami, it doesn't bring a wicket. This is short and angled at the body. Jack Leach leans back trying to sway away from the line of the ball but lets his bat dangle. The ball goes off the face of the bat and quickly towards first slip. Virat Kohli over there mistimes his jump and the ball goes in and out of his palms. Should have taken that one!
FOUR BYES! Shami loses his line this time. Bowls it way outside the leg stump, moving away a bit. Leach leaves it and it beats Rishabh Pant as well and goes to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On a length, close to the off pole and this time the ball holds its line. Jonny Bairstow makes a watchful leave.
Back of a length, around off. Bairstow hangs back to defend.
Very tight line on off stump, Jonny Bairstow blocks it out towards silly mid off.
Goes fuller this time, close to the off stump. Bairstow lets it through to the keeper.
Bowls it down the leg side, it's left alone.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Shami steams in from 'round the wicket and delivers it on a good length outside off, Leach leaves it with ease on this occasion.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Back of a length, around off, shaping away a hint, Jack Leach tries to defend from the back foot but edges it behind. It falls in front of third slip.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The nightwatchman falls without doing his job. He consumed just 5 balls in his stay and never looked convincing. Shami continues with his 'round the wicket angle, serves it on a length around off and it leaves the batter with the seam movement. Jack Leach stands back and feels for it inside the line, only to edge it behind. Rishabh Pant completes an easy catch and England have now lost half their side. They trail by 333 runs.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammad Shami

Commentary: Darts it in full, around off, Ben Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
Angling in from around off, on a good length, Stokes stays on the back foot and defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length, around off and angling in, Stokes gives the bowler charge and then defends it down.
Fuller in length, around middle, Jonny clips it off his pads to mid-wicket.
This time Bumrah pulls his length back a bit, delivers it around off and Bairstow defends it from the back foot.
Bumrah continues to be at the batter. On a length around middle, Bairstow defends it from the crease to mid-wicket.
That's a real tempter. Fuller in length and outside off, swinging in the air a bit, Jonny Bairstow resists the temptation and makes a leave.
Angling down the leg side, on a length, Bairstow tucks it down to fine leg and takes a single.

Jasprit Bumrah switches to 'round the wicket for the final ball of the day's play. He dishes out an outswinger, on a good length outside off, Ben Stokes makes a watchful leave. That will be Stumps on Day 2.
Some swing there for Shami! The line though is down the leg side, Jonny Bairstow tries to flick but misses.
Better line this time. In the channel outside off, on a length and there is not much movement on this occasion, Jonny shoulders arms.

Swing and a miss! Back of a length and wide outside off, Jonny Bairstow stands back to slap it through the line but misses. Rishabh Pant moves across to his right to collect the ball but the ball swerves to his left and he gets a bit wrong-footed as he collects.
On a good length and outside off, moving away, Jonny Bairstow allows it through. Pant drops the ball this time while attempting to collect it.
After bowling a few outswingers, Shami attempts to deliver an inswinger. He fails to control his line though and slips it down the leg side. Bairstow tries to flick again off his pads but misses.
Around off, on a length, Bairstow pushes it out with an angled bat to point. Looks for a run but it is not on.
Angles in a full ball, around off, Ben Stokes gets on the front foot and defends it to the off side.
Beaten! Stokes tries to use his feet to counter the movement but fails. It's an outswinger, on a length and outside off, Stokes ends up pushing and missing inside the line.
Back of a length, around off, Stokes rocks back and defends it down with a straight bat.
Just ahead of a good length, around off, again Stokes covers the angle and defends it towards mid on. It's a no ball for overstepping. We saw plenty of overstepping from Bumrah on Day 2 as well.
FOUR! Fine shot! Fuller in length, around middle and angling in, Stokes leans across and flicks it with good timing through mid-wicket.

Streaky this time. Bumrah serves it on a length around off and gets it to straighten a hint off the seam. Stokes tries to work it across the line with the angle of the bowler but it takes the leading edge. The ball rolls through cover-point and they cross.
Keeps it full and around off, Jonny Bairstow defends it from the crease to short cover.
Shami runs in from 'round the wicket for the southpaw. Delivers it on a length and outside off, Stokes allows it through.
Another delivery on a good length, outside off and angling in, Stokes steps forward to cover the line and shoulders arms.

FOUR! Stokes is ready to play his shots. Jumps down the track to a length ball outside off and smashes it over the bowler's head for a boundary. Brendon McCullum likes it and claps for the shot. That's the approach they want!
Back of a length and around off, Ben taps it down to cover-point and takes a single.

Beaten all ends up! Banana swing for Shami. He gets it to curl back in a long way from outside off. On a length, Bairstow doesn't account for the movement and attempts for a loose drive through the line. He is beaten on the inside edge.
This time Jonny perfectly covers the line and pushes it to mid off.

Ouch! Stokes is down on his haunches. Back of a length, around off and angling in at 142 kph. Stokes attempts to defend from the back foot but gets an inside edge onto the box. The English skipper catches his breath and gets ready to face the music.
Slightly short in length and close to off, Stokes stays back to push inside the line and inside-edges it past the stumps. It rolls towards short fine leg and they cross.

That's a snorter! Extra zip and movement off the surface. Bumrah clocks 145 kph this time and serves it on a shortish length around off. Jonny Bairstow stays back to defend the ball but it straightens late to beat the bat. Pant collects it over his head.
Beaten again! Angling in, on a length outside off at 139 kph, Jonny pokes at it and is beaten by the away movement.
Quicker again, darts it in on middle, on a length, Bairstow blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and around off, at 143 kph, Bairstow flicks it off the inner edge to fine leg and picks up a single. Probing over from Bumrah comes to an end.

Oh dear, the bounce has saved Jonny there! Shami delivers it on a length, around off and nipping in, Bairstow tries to drive but is beaten on the inside edge again. It goes over the off pole. Kohli is quite animated there, having a word with Jonny and the umpire intervenes immediately.

BEATEN AGAIN! Shami is toying with Jonny Bairstow. Fools him this time with a well-cooked outswinger. On a length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow aims for a big shot down the ground but misses. Virat Kohli is again vocal there in the slip cordon, making sure that the batter knows who is bossing the game at the moment.
This one is short but down the leg side, an easy leave for Jonny who is feeling suffocated at the moment.

Streaky! Shami serves it on a length and outside off, nipping away, Bairstow throws his bat it and slices it behind point. Jadeja chases it down and the batters get three runs. It's good for England that Jonny is now away from strike.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Stokes gets across the stumps and defends it late. It goes off the splice of his bat to the slip cordon.
Width there outside off, short in length, Stokes slaps it through the line but finds Mohammed Siraj at point.
Slightly short in length, around off, Jonny goes on the back foot and pushes it to covers.
Fraction short and close to off, Bairstow goes on the back foot and steers it through point for a single.
Movement and extra bounce off the deck, at 90 mph. This one is on a length and around off, Stokes tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It deflects to covers and they cross.
Aims for a glory ball, the yorker, but it's too full and around leg, Jonny Bairstow clips it through square leg and collects a couple of runs.

FOUR! This will make Bairstow feel a lot better. Fuller in length, around off, there is no movement and Jonny hits it through the line. He lofts it down the ground, over mid off and picks up a boundary.
A touch short in length and around off, Bairstow guides it through the gap between covers and backward point. They take two runs.
Some movement off the pitch there. Shami serves it on a good length outside off, shaping away, Stokes leaves.
FOUR! That's spanked! Short in length, wide outside off, Stokes camps back and whacks it over covers for a cracking boundary. He has looked good this morning.
Around middle, on a length, Stokes uses the angle of the bowler and works it to the left of mid on for a run.
FOUR! Bairstow goes aerial and fetches another boundary. It's on a length and outside off, angling in, Jonny again hits through the line and lifts it down the ground, over mid off, for a boundary.

Well bowled! Shami serves it on a length, around off, Jonny Bairstow tries to play straight but it takes the inner edge and goes behind square leg. Good aggressive running between the wickets and they get two runs.

Beauty! Shami finishes the over with a brilliant outswinger. It's around off, on a good length, Jonny Bairstow tries to defend but it moves away late to beat the outside edge. 21 runs in the last two overs, so England are trying to dominate the bowlers.
Shortish delivery, around leg, Stokes walks down the track and taps it down to the off side.
Siraj digs it in short, around leg, Stokes turns inside the crease but then decides not to unveil his pull shot.
Pitches it up, around middle and off, Stokes plays close to his body and defends it towards backward point.
Slightly short in length, around off, Stokes goes back and hits it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! A short-arm jab from Jonny and it scoots away to the fence. Siraj angles in a shortish ball around off, Jonny Bairstow stays on the back foot and whips it through mid-wicket. Not much follow-through of his bat but excellent wristwork as it beats the diving effort of the fielder in the deep.

FOUR! Bairstow is growing in confidence now, ominous signs for India. The sledging from Kohli has not worked. Fuller and around off, Jonny Bairstow goes aerial again and smacks it over covers for a boundary.

PUT DOWN! Shardul Thakur has dropped the skier. Costly, costly miss. Massive in the context of the game. Shami has been extremely unlucky this morning. Short in length, around off, Ben Stokes steps back and tries to hammer it across the line but it takes the toe end of his bat. Thakur settles underneath it at covers, tries to reverse cup it but spills. They cross.
FOUR! Runs are coming thick and fast now. Fuller in length, around middle, Jonny Bairstow uses his wrists and flicks it firmly through square leg. The 50-run stand comes up!
FOUR! Jonny is in the mood! Doesn't try to hit it hard this time, just lofts it down the ground. Fuller in length, around middle, Jonny Bairstow lifts it over mid on and gains another boundary.
Back of a length, around off, defended from the back foot to the off side.
Short again, around off, Jonny uses the angle and pulls it over square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Stokes drives it down to mid on where the fielder makes a diving stop. A single is taken. England have smashed 41 runs in the last 4 overs.

Slight hesitation but no harm is done. A touch short in length, around middle, Stokes turns it in the gap at mid-wicket and picks up a single as the bowler runs after it. Siraj then moves out as Ravindra Jadeja attacks the ball and the batters turn down the plan to take the second run.
Swing and a miss! Not short enough to pull, it's around off, Jonny Bairstow still tries to play the horizontal bat shot and misses.
Angles in a length ball on middle, Jonny eases it to the right of mid on for a single.
Short in length, around off, Stokes goes back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Mayank Agarwal (sub) makes a neat stop near the fence. Three runs taken.
FIFTY FOR BAIRSTOW! His purple patch continues. Fuller in length and outside off, Jonny hits it without much timing to mid off and picks up a single. The English crowd applauds.
Back of a length, around leg, Stokes steps back and runs it down to third man for a run.
Almost edges it behind! A premeditated charge from Stokes, the length though is short and it whistles past the top edge of his bat. It's called a no ball for overstepping.
Misfield! Shortish and around off, it's punched to covers where the fielder misfields and deflects it to the right of mid off. They decide not to cross.
Around off, on a length, Stokes pushes it with an angled bat to point.

DID THAT CARRY? Yes. Bumrah has dropped a sitter. Stokes is living a charmed life. Short in length and outside off, Stokes smacks it down the ground, it's aerial towards mid off where Jasprit Bumrah goes on his knees to catch it but fails to hold on. Two lives for Ben.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bumrah has redeemed himself with a blinder. Stokes runs out of his luck. This is a big moment in the game. India have got the opening they were looking for all morning. 'Lord' Thakur, the man with the golden arm, has done it once more. Shortish again, around off, Stokes steps back to make room and attempts to whack it down the ground. He though fails to find the middle of his bat and once again hits it aerially towards mid off. This time Bumrah is alert, he throws himself to his left and takes a wonderful two-handed catch. Ben is disappointed, and India are ecstatic. Sam Billings arrives.
Howout: c Jasprit Bumrah b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Full and angling down the leg side, Billings flicks it with exquisite timing through square leg and opens his account with a boundary.
Fuller again, around middle, Sam pushes it down to mid on. Eventful over.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and pushes it towards mid off.
Fuller and around off, Jonny drives it to covers and takes a single.
Billings forces a full ball to covers and looks for a run, it's not on.
Sliding down the leg side, fuller in length, Billings clips it through square leg for one.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow will continue to play his shots. Fuller in length and around off, Jonny takes the aerial route again as he hits it over mid off for a boundary.
Shardul Thakur starts this over with a straight delivery on a good length. Sam Billings defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes a fraction fuller this time and shaping away from outside off. Sam Billings is content to leave this one alone. Thakur oversteps and is called a no ball.
Good-length delivery on off, Sam Billings defends this confidently.
Full once again outside off. Sam Billings strides forward and taps it to the off side. Jonny Bairstow looks for a single that is not there.
Slightly short this time outside off. Beats the outside edge of the bat.
Good length once again and on off, Sam Billings is happy to just defend these deliveries.
Wide outside off and full, Sam Billings does not offer a shot.
FOUR! Up and over! Bairstow continues to play his shots! On middle, this is flicked over mid-wicket for a boundary.
In the air but safe! Short in length and on middle, Jonny Bairstow top-edges his attempted pull but luckily for him, it falls safely at long leg. They cross.
On a length outside off, Sam Billings looks to block it but misses.
Goes outside off again, Sam Billings guides it to gully and takes a quick single.
Slightly shorter in length this time, Jonny Bairstow pulls it through mid-wicket. A good stop by the fielder at the boundary line. They take a couple of runs.
Fuller one this time, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards the leg side for one at square leg.

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is seeing the ball really well here! Shardul Thakur bangs this in short and gives Jonny Bairstow enough width to place it over the slips for a boundary to the vacant third man region!
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries get Jonny Bairstow into the 70s! This one is wide as well and on a good length. Jonny Bairstow times this beautifully through point for the second boundary of the over!
Shardul Thakur goes full and closer to the stumps. Jonny Bairstow defends this down the pitch.
Good-length delivery outside off, Jonny Bairstow plays this with soft hands towards covers and rushes across for a single.
Shardul Thakur varies his length here and goes fuller outside off. Sam Billings fends this off towards cover.
Sam Billings gets beaten as he tries to feel for the ball. Shardul Thakur bowls this outside off on a good length, with shape away from the batter.
Lands it on a length and down the middle, Jonny Bairstow eases it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Jonny Bairstow guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
On a length and on leg, Jonny Bairstow looks to pull it but the ball hits his thigh and rolls towards the off side.
SIX! This is brilliant and well connected. Siraj bowls a shorter one on off, Jonny Bairstow pulls it over backward square leg for a maximum.
Slightly shorter and on off, Jonny Bairstow eases it towards the off side.
On a length and on leg, Jonny Bairstow looks to play at it but the ball hits his pads. They take a quick single.
Good from Shardul Thakur as he gets this on a good length outside off. Jonny Bairstow plays this towards gully.

Just short of Cheteshwar Pujara at mid-wicket! Shardul Thakur goes on a length and angles this into the pads, takes some pace off, and gets Jonny Bairstow to mistime his flick in the air towards mid-wicket. Shardul Thakur almost had his second!
Good-length delivery once again outside off and angling in. Jonny Bairstow is firmly behind this one.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Jonny Bairstow here! Shardul Thakur goes full and angling into the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks this casually through square leg for a one-bounce four!

SIX! Jonny Bairstow hammers this one and is taking Shardul Thakur to the cleaners! The bowler pulls his length back a fraction and pitches it in line with the stumps. Jonny Bairstow heaves this high and long into the stands over the mid-wicket region for a biggie!
Huge appeal for LBW but India are just being hopeful here! Slightly full and going down leg, Jonny Bairstow misses the line of the ball as it hits his pads.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off, Jonny Bairstow goes back in his crease and plays it down with soft hands towards the off side.
On a length and on off, Sam Billings eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls it on middle this time, Sam Billings flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On off this time, Jonny Bairstow drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Goes on off again and on a good length, Jonny Bairstow defends it towards the off side.
This one lands on a good length and down the middle, this is eased towards the mid on fielder.
Single to end the over. A low full toss, Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.

NOT OUT! A spike on UltraEdge which means there is an inside edge! Hence, Bairstow reviewed it. Kohli knew this though. This is angled into middle, slightly shorter. Bairstow looks to whip it over the mid-wicket fence but gets an inside edge onto the pads. An appeal and the finger is raised. Bairstow signals the 'T' immediately. Replays show that he survives to fight yet another day.

Shardul Thakur bowls this on a good length outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps this through backward point and runs quickly to get a couple of runs. A 50-run partnership between these two and most runs have come from the bat of Jonny Bairstow! 200 up as well!
Closer to the stumps this time and a fraction full. Jonny Bairstow knocks this back down the pitch.
FOUR! Innovative from Sam Billings!
On the fuller side again, looking for some swing but there is none. It is pushed back to the bowler who misfields but no runs as it goes to mid off.
That is a beauty! Movement of the deck there! Drags his length back, it lands on off and then moves away. Bairstow is beaten as he tries to defend. Finally, Thakur's over comes to an end.
FOUR! Clipped away! Runs continue to flow and Billings moves into double figures. On the pads, he feeds on such deliveries, clips it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
A run after the boundary! On middle, Billings works it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end. Gives the man who is on 95 the strike.
Tap and run! Bairstow is now a boundary away from his third consecutive ton. On off, Bairstow pushes it towards covers for one more.

FOUR! Off the toe end! England won't care how they come. Outside off, Billings goes for a flashy drive, it goes off the toe end of the bat down to the third man fence. The second boundary in the over and third after the resumption. One more of those and England will avoid the follow-on.
Back of a length and on off, Billings blocks.
Well played and really good running between the wickets! Length and on off, Billings lets the ball come to him. He pushes it towards covers and gets to the other end. Retains strike.
Two more! ENGLAND AVOID THE FOLLOW-ON! On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Length and on off, Billings defends it solidly.
Slips this one down the leg side, Billings looks to flick but misses.
Corrects his line and length, bowls it on off, blocked.
Another quick run! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.

NO BALL AND FOUR BYES! Quite honest of Bairstow there to say it was not off the gloves! Short and down the leg side. Bairstow looks to pull but misses. Pant dives to his left, it hits the glove and goes down to the fine leg fence. The umpire asks Bairstow whether it hit the glove and he says no. The no ball is indicated as Thakur oversteps and byes signalled as well.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! 100 for Bairstow! Yet another stunning, stunning knock! His third in a row in this format. This guy is in some form and the way he is scoring these runs is just unreal! Yet again coming to England's rescue. Still, a long way to go though and he knows he needs a big one here. For now, he is soaking in the applause from the crowd and the dressing room. Bairstow gets there with yet another immaculate shot. Back of a length around off, this is punched sweetly through cover-point. The fielder in the deep, Ravindra Jadeja, runs to his right, he slips a bit as his ankle twists and lets it through. Jonny is running in celebration. Really nice gesture from Kohli too as we see him clapping. Well deserved!
Good length and on off, this lands and moves away. Billings looks to defend but is beaten.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
BEATEN AGAIN! Billings can probably leave these deliveries! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Sam has a push at it but is beaten.
Lands it on a length again, on off, this is pushed to covers.
Gets this one to jag back in but it is well outside off. Left alone.
Edged but short! Well short actually! Length and on off, this lands and moves away again. Billings pushes at it, it goes off the outside edge but lands short of the second slip fielder.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one. Another no ball from Thakur.
On off, this is blocked.
Another one on a length and on off, kept out.

Safe! Just out of the reach of Bumrah! On middle, Sam Billings steps out and looks to flick it but closes the face of the bat early. It goes off the leading edge just over Bumrah at mid on who tracks back and then stretches one hand out. Two runs.
Now an easy run towards Bumrah at mid on as he had moved back a little. On middle, this is pushed gently and Sam rushes across to the other end.
Yet another no ball! Thakur is probably struggling with his run-up here. Lands it on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Yet another one! This is not good, really not good. On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, Bairstow pushes it through covers for one.
On off, this is kept out nicely.
Back of a length and on off, Jonny Bairstow gets behind the line and keeps it out.
On off, Bairstow pushes it to covers.
Outside off, this is guided to point.
Goes for the yorker but this is down the leg side. Bairstow looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
On middle, kept out.
That has just missed the off pole! A very good yorker, on off, Billings with the high bat lift, is late in getting his bat down. It hits the toe end and rolls past the off pole.
Flatter and on middle, blocked.
Impact outside off! Flatter and around off, Bairstow goes down on one knee and looks to play the paddle scoop but misses to get hit on the pads.
Attacks the stumps again. Bairstow defends it.
Really well bowled! Sees Bairstow coming down the track and shortens his length. Bairstow looks to defend but this turns away a little, it goes off the outer half through point for one.
On middle, Billings plays it back to the bowler.
A dot to end! A tidy over from Jadeja to begin with. We also saw a hint of turn for him. On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.

Oohhh... straight through Jonny! This is a serious seed. Bumrah hurls it on a length, around off and nipping in, Bairstow tries to defend but it goes through his defense and flies over the stumps. A lovely diving take from Pant, to his left.
Edgy! Around off, on a length, Bairstow pushes at it and edges it past the slip cordon for two.
Angles in a length ball around off, this time Jonny defends it from the middle of his bat.
Fullish and on middle, Jonny Bairstow wrists it down to mid on.

HUGE SHOUT FOR AN LBW! The finger stays down. Seems to be going down the leg side. Jasprit Bumrah consults his players and we hear someone saying - 'Le le!' Means take it. The Indian captain takes the DRS. Coming to the delivery - Bumrah attempts to nail a yorker but it turns out to be a sharp low full toss, around leg at 145 kph. Jonny Bairstow is beaten for pace and fails to keep it out. He is hit on the pads but the umpire disagrees with the appeal. DRS time! No bat is involved and the Ball Tracking confirms that it's missing the stumps.
Delivers it on a length and around off, Jonny strokes it from the back foot to covers.
Flighted and full around off, Sam walks down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Slower through the air, around off, Billings pushes it with an angled bat to point for a run.
Fires it in, quicker and fuller on off, Jonny presses forward and defends it to covers.
The line is a bit straight, Bairstow moves back and tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Jadeja goes short, around middle, Billings moves back and punches it towards mid-wicket. The mid-wicket fielder intervenes and stops it to his left.
Another punch from the back foot by Billings, this time straight to the mid-wicket fielder.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! A sharp catch by Virat Kohli at first slip. Mohammad Shami had put in all the investment in the morning session and now he gets rich dividends. Jonny Bairstow is out of here but not before entertaining one and all. This one is served wide outside off, at 139 kph, on a good length, Jonny sees the width and decides to attack it. It though has a little bit of away shape and that's enough to catch the outside edge. Kohli snaps it next to his face. A champion knock is over. England trail by 175 runs.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Mohammad Shami

Commentary: Back of a length, around leg and angling down, Broad tries to work it away but misses.

FOUR BYES! England will take all the extras from here on. Shami digs it in short, around middle, it's well-directed and Broad tries to save his head. He ducks late and it flies behind the keeper for a boundary.
Around off, on a fuller length, Broad taps it down to covers and rushes to the other end, as to save his life. There is a misfield but no extra run is taken.
Gets on the front foot and pushes a length ball to covers.
Slightly short and on off, Sam punches to the left of Ravindra Jadeja at covers and steals a single.
Siraj begins with a length ball outside off, Billings reaches out and plays it down towards backward point.
Back of a length, around off, Sam steers it through point and picks up a single.
Fraction short and around off, Broad stands back inside the crease and punches it towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj bowls short, outside off at 141 kph, Stuart Broad hangs back to pull but it takes the top edge and goes straight up in the air. Rishabh Pant rushes forward from his mark and accepts the skier easily. Two quick wickets for India and now the English tail has been exposed. The hosts trail by 168 runs.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: On a length and outside off, Sam Billings drives it through covers and picks up a couple of runs.
A bumper, targeting the body, Billings fails to sway away and takes a blow on his body. End of a successful over.
FOUR! Shortish ball, around leg, Matthew Potts goes on his toes and somehow tries to work it away. It pings him on the gloves and races away to the fine leg fence.
Swing and a miss! Short and around off, Matthew Potts gives the charge, aiming for the long on fence but connects only with thin air.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Gets behind the line and blocks it towards the bowler.
Edged but safe! A length ball, around off, straightening a bit, Matthew Potts tries to play straight but it takes the outside edge and drops in front of Shreyas Iyer at second slip.
Wide called for height! A bouncer, around leg, Potts moves away and Pant jumps to collect it.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Potts mistimes his shot back to Shami.

FOUR! Innovative from Sam Billings! Goes full outside off, Sam Billings gets across the line of the stumps and paddles this to the fine leg boundary! Sam Billings is going into the shorter-format mode!
Good-length delivery outside off, Sam Billings gets an inside edge onto his pads and is not worried about taking the single and giving Matthew Potts strike.
Tempting delivery wide from off stump and full. Matthew Potts tries to thump it but gets beaten.
Mohammed Siraj bangs this in short and angles it down leg side. Matthew Potts goes for the pull but does not connect and Rishabh Pant takes it well behind the wickets diving to his left.
Good-length delivery outside off. Matthew Potts does well to defend this one.
Mohammed Siraj ends with a yorker in line with the stumps. Matthew Potts gets his bat down in time and digs it out.

Touch fuller and on off, Sam Billings dances down the track and looks to loft it but miscues it over extra cover. The ball was in the air for quite a long but falls in no man's land. Sam Billings gets a lucky escape. They take a couple of runs.
On off again, Sam Billings pushes it to wide mid off for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Matthew Potts blocks it away.
Shorter and on middle, Matthew Potts gets in two minds but ducks under it in the end.
FOUR! On a length and on leg, Matthew Potts flicks it in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket for a boundary.
Sharp yorker down the leg side, Matthew Potts defends it to mid on.

OUT! TIMBER! Siraj has yet another one! The last recognized batter is out of here! This is on a length and around off, jags back in a touch. Billings looks to guide it down to third man as he tries to play it with an open face. It is against the movement though. The ball hits the inside edge and then smashes into the stumps. England still trail by 149 runs.
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Siraj is bowling with fire! Aiming for the stumps on a good length. James Anderson covers the stumps and fends the ball towards the leg side.

What is happening here? Mohammed Siraj is celebrating a wicket but Virat Kohli is saying it is not out. The umpire agrees and Mohammed Siraj looks stunned. Excellent delivery bowled on a good length, shaping away from the left-handed batter. James Anderson is beaten all ends up but manages not to nick it.
FOUR! Strays down the leg side this time and James Anderson gets a tickle onto this one and plays it to the fine leg boundary to get England some valuable runs!

Mohammed Siraj comes 'round the wicket now and bowls a beauty of a delivery. Gets the ball to pitch on off stump and shape away, and beats James Anderson on the inside edge as he plays wide from his body.
Slightly shorter and wide from the stumps, James Anderson gets a thickish edge past slip. There is a half-stop from the slip fielder which allows the batters to take a couple of runs.
On a length and outside off, Matthew Potts swings his bat but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and carries towards the vacant mid off region.
Goes outside off again, James Anderson looks to block it but misses.
This was similar to the last delivery, James Anderson looks to block it but misses again.
This one lands on a length and just outside off nipping it in, James Anderson dances down the track to play at it but misses again. This is excellent bowling from Mohammad Shami.
Touch fuller and on middle this time, James Anderson blocks it away towards the off side.
Touch fuller and outside off again, James Anderson looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! England is being stubborn here! Mohammed Siraj bowls this one short angling down leg, Matthew Potts does not get a hold of it but still manages to make it run to fine leg boundary for four more runs!

SIX! Matthew Potts is playing a bit of a cameo here! This one is dispatched over the square leg boundary for a maximum. Mohammed Siraj goes back of a length but the ball does not rise as much as he wanted. Sits up nicely for Matthew Potts to get a hold of it! England trail by 132 runs now!

OUT! CAUGHT! England are all out for 284! On a length and outside off, Matthew Potts looks to push it towards the off side but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries towards the second slip fielder where Shreyas Iyer takes it in his second attempt. Umpires decide to go upstairs. The soft signal is out. The ball seemed to have touched the ground but the decision goes in favour of the umpires. Strange. A mix of boos and cheers from the crowd. Potts shakes his head as he returns. That's a debatable decision.
Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: James Anderson begins with a testing line outside off on a good length. Shubman Gill leaves it alone.
FOUR! Off the mark in typical Shubman Gill style! Full and outside off, Shubman Gill gets forward and lets the ball meet his bat as he plays this through mid off for his first boundary!

OUT! CAUGHT! James Anderson is doing what he does best! Strikes early for England and this opening stand has been broken in the first over itself! Full once again outside off. Shubman Gill trying to be positive plays at it and gets a thick edge to second slip where Zak Crawley is alert! India have lost an early wicket.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b James Anderson

Commentary: Good-length delivery on middle. Hanuma Vihari fends this towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! James Anderson looking lethal with the new ball! Length delivery pitching just outside off, keeps its line, and beats Hanuma Vihari all ends up.
James Anderson serves this on a good length once again in line with the stumps. Hanuma Vihari is well behind this one as he knocks it down the pitch.
On a length and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
On off this time and much fuller, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards the mid off fielder.
Fuller one again angling it into the batter, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block it but the ball hits his pads and rolls back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the fielder at short cover.
Good-length delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms and lets it go.
A low full toss, almost a yorker, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it as the ball bounces back towards Stuart Broad. Oh, its a no ball.
That was close! Goes fuller and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to play at it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls past the stumps and towards short fine leg. They take a single.
James Anderson goes full outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends this to covers.

FOUR! Gets this one past fourth slip with soft hands! Slightly short and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara gets the outside part of his bat to the ball and plays it along the ground towards third man for a boundary!
Straight this time on a good length. Cheteshwar Pujara defends this back to the bowler.
Big appeal from the English players but this is going down leg. James Anderson goes full and attacks the pads, the batters scamper across from a single.
Great shape in the ball but quite wide and slightly short, Hanuma Vihari plays inside the line of the ball and keeps his bat away.

James Anderson gets a nick but falls short of two diving fielders! Good-length delivery outside off, Hanuma Vihari hangs his bat out and gets a thick edge. Some players claim the catch others know it has fallen short.
Slightly shorter one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards the off side.
This one lands outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara slashes it towards the gully. The fielder just gets his hands to it and rolls away. They take a single.
On a length and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller and on off, Hanuma Vihari looks to play at it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg. They take a single.
FOUR! Brilliant shot. Outside off and on a length, Cheteshwar Pujara waits for the ball and punches it through point for a boundary.
This one lands outside off and nips back in, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone. That was a tight leave.
Good movement for James Anderson as he bowls this on a good length on off. Hanuma Vihari sees this well and defends confidently.
Great rhythm from James Anderson as he consistently bowls outside off on a good length. Hanuma Vihari fends this towards mid-wicket.
This one is a fraction shorter and wide from off stump. Hanuma Vihari raises his hand and lets it through to the keeper.
Attacks the stumps from a good length. Hanuma Vihari is solidly behind this one.
James Anderson serves this slightly back of a length and outside off, Hanuma Vihari plays inside the line of the ball and leaves it alone.
James Anderson bowling in the outside off stump channel and getting the ball to shape away. Hanuma Vihari mocks a defensive shot and leaves the ball alone.
Slightly shorter and angling into the batter, Cheteshwar Pujara hops a bit and defends it towards the off side.
Delivers it just outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves this one as well.
Another one outside off and nips back in, Cheteshwar Pujara makes another tight leave.
Bowls it on middle this time, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it as the ball bounces towards the fielder at slips.
Bowls it on middle again, Cheteshwar Pujara clips it towards square leg for one.
Straying down leg side from a good length, Cheteshwar Pujara works this to fine leg for a single.
James Anderson has got his radar off slightly here. This one is wide from off stump and full. Hanuma Vihari shoulders his arms to it.
This time he goes closer to the stumps and bowls it full. Hanuma Vihari gets his front foot forward and knocks it towards cover.
That is more like the James Anderson we know. The outside off stump line on a good length, gets Hanuma Vihari playing for it and beats him on his outside edge.
James Anderson attacks the off stump from a good length, Hanuma Vihari does well to get behind this and fend it towards the offside.

FOUR LEG BYES! Some easy runs for India here! Full and angling down the leg side, Hanuma Vihari tries to work this fine but misses. Still manages to get a tickle off his pads towards the fine leg boundary for four leg byes.
Shorter one outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Goes outside leg and fuller in length, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick it but misses.
Bowls it outside off, this is left alone as well.
Delivers it outside off and fuller in length, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards the fielder at mid on.
Another one outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the off side. Hanuma Vihari wanted a single but Pujara sent him back.
This one lands outside off as well, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms at it.
Hanuma Vihari gets off strike with a single through square leg. James Anderson bowls a length delivery on middle.
Phew! That was really close! What a delivery from James Anderson as he pitches this on off from a good length. Beats Cheteshwar Pujara completely and just goes over the off pole!
Full and in line with the stumps, Cheteshwar Pujara works this through point for a single.
James Anderson gets this one to shape in from outside off. Hanuma Vihari works this leg side.
On a good length and outside off. Hanuma Vihari fends this towards the slip cordon where Ben Stokes collects and feigns a catch to get the crowd excited.
Serves this length delivery wide from off stump. Hanuma Vihari happy to leave this one.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Goes on middle, shaping it in, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly off his front foot.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the fielder at gully.
On a length and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
On middle again, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the vacant short leg region.
A maiden to start with. Goes on middle angling it into the batter, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his thigh and rolls back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Hanuma Vihari makes the most of this loose delivery! James Anderson starts off short and wide from off stump, Hanuma Vihari who had been subdued up until now gets to this in a flash and whacks it towards deep point for his first boundary!
James Anderson comes back well as his bowls this outside off from a good length. Lures Hanuma Vihari into a shot and beats him.
Full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari knocks this towards cover.
James Anderson goes wide from this crease and bowls this full on off, Hanuma Vihari fends this with soft hands.
That is a bouncer from James Anderson as he tries to cramp the batter. Hanuma Vihari is prepared and ducks under this one.
James Anderson goes back to bowling full on off. Hanuma Vihari knocks it straight back down the pitch.
Matthew Potts bowls it on a length and down the leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Outside off this time, Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Touch fuller this time and on off, Hanuma Vihari defends it towards the off side.
Outside off again, Hanuma Vihari leaves this one as well.
Some extra bounce and lands it just outside off, Hanuma Vihari looks to defend it but misses.
Fires it on middle, Hanuma Vihari defends it as the ball falls towards his toes.
Jack Leach to bowl that last over before Lunch and he gets massive spin straight away. This one is wide outside off and Cheteshwar Pujara reaches for it but misses.
Full outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara opens the face of the bat and works it through point for a single.
Full and attacking the stumps. Hanuma Vihari steps gets forwards and knocks it towards long on where a misfield allows them to get back for a second.
Jack Leach angles this into the stumps from outside off. Hanuma Vihari solid in defense.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Hanuma Vihari flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace. This is good running between the wickets.
Fuller and on off, Hanuma Vihari cuts it but finds the fielder at point. That will be Tea on Day 3.
Back-of-a-length delivery to begin, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara rises up and plays at it as it falls short of gully.
What a beauty! Cheteshwar Pujara needs to get his focus back! Bowled on a good length just outside off with movement away from the batter. Cheteshwar Pujara plays at it and misses.
Much more solid from Cheteshwar Pujara as he gets well behind this full delivery on off stump.
Full once again and angling in from off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this back to the bowler.
Middle stump line from a good length. Cheteshwar Pujara works this leg side.
On a good length outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara goes back on the crease and plays this towards bacward point.
Lands it outside off angling it in, Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Back of a length and outside off, Hanuma Vihari punches it to covers where the fielder makes a diving stop to his right. They take a single.
On a length and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
Bowls it on leg and fuller in length, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On a length and on leg, Hanuma Vihari flicks it towards the leg side.
Slightly shorter one just outside off, Hanuma Vihari looks to defend it but gets an inside edge and to his pads.
Matthew Potts serves this on a good length and angling into the batter, Cheteshwar Pujara guides this towards mid-wicket.
Goes a fraction fuller and angling in from off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this towards mid on.

FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara just guides this past backward point fielder who dives to his left but can not get to it. Length delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara uses soft hands to play this really well.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off, Cheteshwar Pujara rises up and gets behind this one solidly.
Matthew Potts pulls his length back outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara hangs his bat out to dry when he should be leaving this one alone.
Matthew Potts is wide this time and full, Cheteshwar Pujara covers the stumps with his front foot and leaves the ball alone.
Goes fuller and down the middle, Hanuma Vihari guides it towards the fielder at mid on.
Yorker and on middle, Hanuma Vihari defends it back towards the bowler.
OUT! CAUGHT! This one lands fuller and outside off, Hanuma Vihari looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes towards third slip where Jonny Bairstow takes it safely.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Bowls it outside off, Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, Virat Kohli defends it away.
FOUR! Touch fuller and outside off, Virat Kohli drives it past covers for a boundary. Virat Kohli gets off the mark in style.
Matthew Potts delivers this full and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara gets a stride forward and leaves at the last moment.
Length delivery angling into middle, Cheteshwar Pujara works this off his legs towards fine leg for a single.

Matthew Potts is convinced this one is out! The umpire says there is nothing to it and Ben Stokes does not opt for a review. Good-length delivery outside off, Virat Kohli goes for the ball and his beaten on his outside edge. The sound was from bat hitting pad.

FOUR! Edgy from Virat Kohli as Matthew Potts is looking really good here! On a good length and shaping away from off stump. Virat Kohli comes across to cover the movement but gets a thick edge past third slip for a boundary to third man!
Angles this one in from off stump, Virat Kohli works this wide off mid on for a single.
That is a wonderful over from Matthew Potts as he ends it with another beauty! Great length outside off and beats the outside edge once again!
Goes fuller and down the middle, Virat Kohli defends it towards the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! This one lands fuller and outside off, Virat Kohli creams it past covers for a boundary.
On a length and outside off, Virat Kohli leaves it alone. The keeper fumbles to collect it for the first time.
Fuller and on middle, Virat Kohli hits it back towards the bowler who does it well to block it.
This one lands outside off, Virat Kohli defends it towards the off side.
Fuller and on middle, Virat Kohli defends it back towards the bowler.
Matthew Potts goes full and angles it into the pads, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks this towards mid-wicket.
Full once again outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara is watchful as he lets this one go through.
Good-length delivery outside off stump, shaping in, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this back down the pitch.

There is a review here! Could be for LBW and Caught Behind! There is no bat involved and we go to Ball Tracking! It shows that the ball is going over the stumps and England lose their review! Matthew Potts bowls this on a good length and it nips back in sharply! Hits Cheteshwar Pujara straight on the pads and the England players are convinced!

FOUR! Matthew Potts has been unlucky to not have a few wickets under his belt! He bowls another jaffa of a delivery outside off that beats gets an edge off Cheteshwar Pujara's bat! Falls short between keeper and first slip as neither can get to it and it runs away for a boundary!
Full delivery angling in, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks this wide of mid on and a dive from Stuart Broad saves four runs.
Starts with a fuller and on middle, Virat Kohli defends it solidly.
Goes fuller and on middle, Virat Kohli flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
This one lands on off, Virat Kohli drives it towards the cover fielder.
On a length and outside off, Virat Kohli defends it towards point.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Virat Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Bowls it fuller again and on leg, Virat Kohli eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Matthew Potts goes full on the pads, Cheteshwar Pujara works this through square leg for a brace.
Serves this full once again outside off, defended towards the off side.
Wider from the stumps and full, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it for the keeper to gather.
Another appeal for LBW from England but this one is going down leg as well! Full and angling in as it thuds against the pads.
Delivers this full and a little closer to the stump. Cheteshwar Pujara is looking good in defense.
On a good length outside off. Works this towards point.
Slightly shorter and on off, Virat Kohli looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces back towards the vacant short leg region.
Bowls it outside off, Virat Kohli hits it but finds the fielder at covers.
On a length and outside off angling it in, Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Fuller in length and on off, Virat Kohli drives it towards the mid off fielder.
On a length and on off, Virat Kohli defends it solidly.
A maiden for James Anderson. On off again, Virat Kohli defends it away.
Good length and on off, defended.
Angled into the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
On the stumps, straightens a touch, Kohli plays it late and onto the ground.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Slightly fuller and on off, Pujara strokes it to mid off.
Well played in the end! On off, this one jags back in. Pujara works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
A short one, a rare short one, ducked under.
On off, shortish, Pujara hangs back and pushes it through covers for one.
On off, this is pushed to mid off for one.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on middle, Pujara evades it well.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.
On off, this is blocked nicely.
Outside off, not played at.
Another bumper, it is ducked under.
On off, defended well.
On the stumps, Kohli gets right behind the line and defends it.
He was late on that one. Probably was in two minds. Outside off, Kohli initially wanted to leave it but then sees it coming back in. He looks to put bat on ball but is beaten.
Well fielded! On middle, Kohli flicks it but the man at mid-wicket dives to his left and stops it.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A little too full and Kohli puts it away. He is into the 20s! Fuller and on off, Kohli shows the full face of the bat and creams it through mid off. This one races away to the fence in no time.
Another wonderfully timed stroke! On middle, Kohli shows the full face of the bat again and strokes it to mid on.
Good length and on off, blocked well.
Another one on the off pole, kept out.
Well wide outside off, left alone.
Another harmless nut! Outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Three leaves in a row as this is yet again not on the stumps.
NO BALL! Yet another one, seen a lot in this game so far! Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, Pujara works it through mid-wicket for one.
James Anderson goes really short this time and wide from the stumps. Cheteshwar Pujara goes on his toes and leaves it alone.
Goes back to bowling on a length outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara does the same and lets it go.
Pulls the length back a fraction outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara is showing us an exhibition of leaves.
James Anderson is inconsistent with his length here as he goes full outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara is doing what he does best and not playing at it.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara finally decides to play and slashes this to point.
Finally a good delivery just outside off, shaping away from Cheteshwar Pujara as he gets beaten.
This one lands outside leg and fuller in length, Virat Kohli looks to flick at it but misses.
An inswinger from Ben Stokes. Bowls it outside off angling it into the batter, Virat Kohli lets it go. That was a tight leave.
Shorter one on middle, Virat Kohli ducks underneath it.
This is on off, Virat Kohli defends it solidly.

OUT! EDGED AND DROPPED... NO, WAIT! IT HAS BEEN TAKEN! Kohli has to walk back! That is a brute of a delivery. Surely Kohli must be wondering, why him? We have hardly seen any balls misbehave and Kohli was looking so good but he gets a brute of a delivery here. Not a lot he could do with that. Stokes, the English skipper, breaks the stand that was going along so smoothly. This is on a length and around off, it lands, takes off and moves away. Kohli pushes at it ahead of his body, the ball flies off the shoulder of the bat towards Billings. He does not pouch it but Root at first slip is alert and he takes a good one-handed reflex catch on the rebound. Is this the opening England needed? India are effectively 207 for 3.
Howout: c Joe Root b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Fuller on leg, Rishabh Pant flicks it towards the leg side for one.
Stuart Broad is going to go 'round the wicket to the left-hander. Serves this full and outside off, Rishabh Pant leaves this one alone.
Adjusts his line, and gets it angling in from off, Rishabh Pant works this towards mid-wicket for a single.

A little bit of extra bounce for Stuart Broad as he pitches this on a length and on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara gets on top of the delivery and gets his gloves to it as he plays it down. Does a little bit of damage to himself though and the physio is called on.
Stuart Broad bangs this one short but it is going down the leg side. Cheteshwar Pujara turns around and watches it go to the keeper.

Stuart Broad serves this one full on middle, keeps really low, and gets the toe end of Cheteshwar Pujara's bat and goes towards first slip. The England players feel it may have hit the pad and go up in appeal while Joe Root takes a shy at the stumps but misses. Gives three runs as overthrows in the process.
FOUR! Pant now gets his first boundary! Full and angling in from around the wicket, Rishabh Pant connects this well past mid-wicket for a good boundary!
On a length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards the leg side.
Slightly shorter down the leg side, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards fine leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, Rishabh Pant looks to play at it but misses.
Another fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant looks to defend it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards backward point for one.
This one lands outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.

A huge appeal but the umpire shakes his head! STOKES REVIEWS! NOT OUT! England do not lose a review though as it is clipping the top of off. It remains the umpire's call. This is a big booming inswinger from well outside off. Pujara lets it be with a big stride forward and takes it on his front pad. A huge appeal but it's turned down. Stokes reviews but in vain.
Much better from Stuart Broad as he decided to go over the wicket. Pitches this on a good length and angling away. Play and a miss from Rishabh Pant.
This one is full and on the pads, Rishabh Pant works this square of mid-wicket for a single.
Straying down leg once more, Cheteshwar Pujara helps this to fine leg for another single.
Serves this really wide from the stumps and full, Rishabh Pant does not go for this one.
Stuart Broad brings the ball in closer to the stumps on a good length. Rishabh Pant judges this one well and leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on middle. Rishabh Pant works this leg side and looks for a single, but is sent back by Cheteshwar Pujara as Stuart Broad rushes to collect the ball.
An inswinger from Ben Stokes, Pujara defends it solidly towards the off side.
Fuller and angling it into the batter, Pujara eases it towards the fielder at covers.
Bowls it on leg this time, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards fine leg for one.
On a length and down the middle, Rishabh Pant blocks it back towards the bowler.
A low full toss with some swing, Rishabh Pant miscues his flick towards covers. They rotate the strike.
Bowls it fuller and down the middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Stuart Broad starts off bowling a length ball on the pads. Rishabh Pant works this towards mid-wicket for a single.
Wide from off stump and full, Cheteshwar Pujara raises his hands and lets the ball go through.
This is delivered full outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara plays this firmly towards covers.
Outside off and stays a little low as it goes on the bounce to the keeper. Stuart Broad needs to make Cheteshwar Pujara play more.
Similar delivery on a good length outside off. Same result as Cheteshwar Pujara continues being patient.
This one is on the off stump line from a good length. Cheteshwar Pujara plays at this and looks solid in defense.
FOUR! Goes fuller and on leg, Rishabh Pant flicks it through backward square leg for a boundary. Amazing wristwork from Rishabh Pant.
Fuller again and down the leg side, Rishabh Pant looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and rolls towards fine leg. The keeper has a long chase to do and he does well. Two leg byes taken.
On leg again, Rishabh Pant clips it towards backward square leg for one.
Shorter one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara waits for the ball and hits it towards gully where the fielder gets his hand to it diving to his left.  They take a couple of runs.
Slightly shorter and on off, this is defended towards the off side.
Back of a length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara hits it towards backward point for a brace.
Stuart Broad starts well with a good-length delivery on middle, Rishabh Pant has to defend this.
Goes full on the pads once again to allow Rishabh Pant to flick this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length delivery outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara knocks this down the pitch.
Angles this one in from outside off on a good length, Cheteshwar Pujara drops this towards the leg side with soft hands.
Gets this one to shape the other way and beats the outside edge! On a good length and draws Cheteshwar Pujara forward into the shot.
Stuart Broad ends the over with a full delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks this towards covers.
Fuller one and on middle, Rishabh Pant flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! What a brilliant shot. On a length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara opens the face of the blade and guides it through backward point for a boundary.
This one lands on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it towards the fielder at mid off.
Fuller one and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to play at it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
Fuller one again on off, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards covers.
Goes fuller again, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards point and straight towards the fielder.

FOUR! There you go! Broad feeds it on a length around middle, Rishabh Pant advances down the track and drags it down to long on for a boundary. The bowler was seen taking evasive action even though it was quite far away. That's scary.
Angles across a length ball, outside off, Pant lets it be.
Another delivery in the corridor outside off, Pant feels for it this time and gets beaten.
A bit shorter this time, outside off, Rishabh Pant has nothing to do with it. He withdraws his bat late though.
Fuller this time, in line with the stumps, it's been clipped to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Puts it full and around off, Pujara pushes it in a controlled manner to cover-point.
Starts with a length ball, outside off, Pant allows it through to the keeper.
Digs it in short, around off, Pant pulls it all along the ground to deep mid-wicket for two runs.
Back of a length, outside off, Pant shoulders arms.
Slightly short and close to off, Pant camps back and punches it through point for one.

Shout for an lbw, not given. A big inswinger from Jimmy. It pitches on a length and outside off, curling back in, Cheteshwar Pujara takes his front leg away from the line of the stumps and then tries to block it with his bat hiding behind the front pad. He is struck on the front pad, the bowler appeals vociferously and then smiles.
Movement into the batter again, around middle, Pujara defends it carefully to the leg side.
Flighted delivery, way wide outside off, Pant leaves.
Tossed up, wide outside off again, Pant is not chasing it.
Root continues to deliver outside off and Pant continues to leave.
Slower through the air, outside off, another leave from Pant.
Flighted and outside off, Pant presses forward and leaves once more.
Quicker and outside off, Pant decides to let it through as well. Maiden.
Shorter and on off, Pujara plays it towards point and wants a run but is sent back. The umpire asks Pujara to not run straight down the pitch.
Outside off, Pujara plays it towards cover again.
Shorter and on off, Pujara guides it to point. Anderson falls in his followthrough. Maybe trying a little too hard. However, there is not a lot of pace now in this wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
On the middle pole, this is defended nicely.
Two to end! Anderson gets a little too straight, this is clipped through square leg for two.
WIDE! That is nice and slow but well wide outside off, turns away further. Wided.
Another one nice and slow outside off, looking to tempt Pant but he gently pushes it to covers.
Slower through the air but this time on off, Pant pushes it to covers.
A little flatter this time and on off, Pant blocks.
FOUR! Whipped away! The length was poor here! It is short and on middle, Pant hangs back and whips it powerfully through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slower through the air but well outside off, not played at.
Testing Pant's patience is Root here! Pant doing well till now! Well wide outside off and slower. Left alone.
From around the wicket, bangs it short. Pujara looks to tap and run as he drops it towards covers but is sent back. He gets a warning for running on the danger area.
Pujara cops a blow! A short one. Pujara is probably in two minds about whether to move out of the way or play at it, in the end, it hits him on the body.
Another short one but outside off, Pujara lets it go. Not sure if this is the right tactic at Anderson's pace.
Goes short again and on middle, Pujara lets it go over him.
Another short one, this does not bounce a lot. Blocked.
Again, the bumper is evaded easily as it is down the leg side. A maiden by Anderson but a harmless one.
Flatter and on off, Pant pushes it through covers for one.

Fifty for Pujara! It has been a grind for him as the going was tough at the start. He weathered the storm earlier on when the ball was new and then as it became easier to score, capitalized on the opportunities. Can he score a ton now? He gets there by working a full toss through mid-wicket for one.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at. Another harmless delivery and the last ball is now coming up.

Was that a chance? Well, if it was, it was a very tough one. Harsh to call it dropped, to be honest! Shorter and outside off, this one stays low. Pant looks to cut but it takes the under-edge. Billings is on his way up but then finds that it's a chance. Goes down low but it doesn't stick. A lucky escape for Pant. THAT IS STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Anderson begins with a delivery on the shorter side around off, Pujara watches the line and then shoulders arms.
There is certainly not much pace on offer from this surface. Slightly short in length and outside off, Pujara tries to punch from the back foot but mistimes it to covers.
This time the line from the bowler moves to middle and leg, it's on a length and Pujara tucks it off his hips to backward square leg for a run. India are away on Day 4!
Good bounce on this delivery. Around off, a bit on the shorter side, Pant leans back, keeps his bat close to his body as he allows it through.
Serves it on a driving length outside off, Pant makes another leave.
Back of a length, close to off, Pant covers the line and leaves it alone. There is some late away movement as it goes past the batter.
Flighted ball, around leg and skidding down, Pujara leaves and the keeper fails to collect. They collect two byes.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Pujara jumps down the track and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up outside off, Pant allows it through.
Flatter and around off, skidding in, Pant stays back and plays it in the gap at covers for a single.
Floated delivery, full and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet again and eases it to mid on.
Loopy and around off, fuller in length, Pujara is quick to run down the track and wrists it to deep mid-wicket. He calls for two but gets only a run.
Anderson delivers it on a good length, in the zone outside off and going almost straight on, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Close to off this time, on a length, Pujara gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Quite wide outside off on this occasion, Pujara offers no shot.

FOUR! That's a beautiful shot! Cheteshwar Pujara loves it there. Back of a length, around off, Pujara eases himself on the back foot and punches it sweetly through cover-point. The ball has lost its hardness and not doing much to bother the batter.

FOUR! Pujara is looking in fine touch and picking the boundaries. Anderson overcorrects his line and length, goes very full and straight, Cheteshwar Pujara leans across and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. The lead is now 271.
A touch short and on off, Pujara goes on the back foot and defends it off the inner half to mid-wicket. It's called a no ball for overstepping. Will the extra ball fetch Jimmy a wicket?
The answer is no. Fuller and around off, Pujara solidly pushes it off his front foot to covers.
Flighted and wide outside off, Pant has nothing to do with it.
FOUR! Here goes Pant! Short in length, outside off and skidding in, Pant rocks back and slaps it through backward point for a boundary.
Short again, outside off, Pant moves back and punches it to covers.
A slider around off, skidding in, Pant goes on the back foot and keeps it out at the last moment.
A low full toss this time, around off, Pant presses forward and drives it past the diving cover fielder for a run.

It's smashed down the ground! Root does well to stop it, partially. Loopy and around off, Pujara walks forward to take it on the full and strokes it back firmly. Root gets a hand to it and deflects it onto the stumps at his end. Pant never moved out though.
Back of a length, around middle and off, Pant goes on his toes and defends it down on the surface.
Angling in from around off, on a length, Pant flicks it softly to the leg side but finds short mid-wicket.
Fraction short, on top of off, Pant camps back and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Extra bounce this time. It's an effort ball from Anderson. He bends his back to bowl it short around off, Pujara climbs on top of the delivery and defends it safely to the off side.

And again. Anderson is getting some steep bounce from a good length around off. Cheteshwar Pujara stays inside the crease and defends it from the splice of his bat. He is clever to withdraw his bottom hand so that if there is an edge, it doesn't carry to the fielders.
Slants a length ball in, around middle, Pujara fails to defend due to the extra bounce again. He is hit high on the thigh pad.
Flatter and shorter, on off, Pant goes on the back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Full and around off, Pujara decides to defend it back from the crease.
Loopy and full, around off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks softly but finds short mid-wicket.
Uses his feet to deal with this full delivery and eases it wide of mid-wicket. Picks up a single.
